  <Name>k__BackingField: John
  fancyName: 
  nickname: jhn
  version: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 433894a244f646848a22a9c7d127b66b, type: 2}
  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Prologue: Christ, the Eternal Word'
      title: 'Prologue: Christ, the Eternal Word'
      number: 1
      content: '  In the beginning the Word already existed.The Word was with God,and
        the Word was God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'He existed in the beginning with God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'God created everything through him,and nothing was created except
        through him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'The Word gave life to everything that was created,[[COMMENT(0)]]and
        his life brought light to everyone.  '
      comments:
      - number: '1:3-4 '
        content: Or <b>and nothing that was created was created except through him.
          The Word gave life to everything.</b>
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'The light shines in the darkness,and the darkness can never extinguish
        it.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '1:5 '
        content: Or <b>and the darkness has not understood it.</b>
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'God sent a man, John the Baptist,[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '1:6 '
        content: Greek <b>a man named John.</b>
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'to tell about the light so that everyone might believe because of
        his testimony. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'John himself was not the light; he was simply a witness to tell about
        the light. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'The one who is the true light, who gives light to everyone, was coming
        into the world.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "He came into the very world he created, but the world didn\u2019t
        recognize him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'He came to his own people, and even they rejected him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'But to all who believed him and accepted him, he gave the right to
        become children of God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "They are reborn\u2014not with a physical birth resulting from human
        passion or plan, but a birth that comes from God.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "So the Word became human[[COMMENT(0)]] and made his home among us.
        He was full of unfailing love and faithfulness.[[COMMENT(1)]] And we have
        seen his glory, the glory of the Father\u2019s one and only Son.  "
      comments:
      - number: '1:14a '
        content: Greek <b>became flesh.</b>
      - number: '1:14b '
        content: Or <b>grace and truth; </b>also in 1:17.
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "John testified about him when he shouted to the crowds, \u201CThis
        is the one I was talking about when I said, \u2018Someone is coming after
        me who is far greater than I am, for he existed long before me.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'From his abundance we have all received one gracious blessing after
        another.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '1:16 '
        content: Or <b>received the grace of Christ rather than the grace of the
          law; </b>Greek reads <b>received grace upon grace.</b>
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "For the law was given through Moses, but God\u2019s unfailing love
        and faithfulness came through Jesus Christ. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: The Testimony of John the Baptist'
      title: The Testimony of John the Baptist
      number: 18
      content: "No one has ever seen God. But the unique One, who is himself God,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        is near to the Father\u2019s heart. He has revealed God to us.  "
      comments:
      - number: '1:18 '
        content: Some manuscripts read <b>But the one and only Son.</b>
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "This was John\u2019s testimony when the Jewish leaders sent priests
        and Temple assistants[[COMMENT(0)]] from Jerusalem to ask John, \u201CWho
        are you?\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '1:19 '
        content: Greek <b>and Levites.</b>
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "He came right out and said, \u201CI am not the Messiah.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "\u201CWell then, who are you?\u201D they asked. \u201CAre you Elijah?\u201D\u201CNo,\u201D
        he replied.\u201CAre you the Prophet we are expecting?\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]\u201CNo.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '1:21 '
        content: Greek <b>Are you the Prophet? </b>See Deut 18:15, 18; Mal 4:5-6.
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "\u201CThen who are you? We need an answer for those who sent us.
        What do you have to say about yourself?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "John replied in the words of the prophet Isaiah:\u201CI am a voice
        shouting in the wilderness,\u2018Clear the way for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s
        coming!\u2019\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '1:23 '
        content: Isa 40:3.
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Then the Pharisees who had been sent '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "asked him, \u201CIf you aren\u2019t the Messiah or Elijah or the
        Prophet, what right do you have to baptize?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "John told them, \u201CI baptize with[[COMMENT(0)]] water, but right
        here in the crowd is someone you do not recognize. "
      comments:
      - number: '1:26 '
        content: Or <b>in; </b>also in 1:31, 33.
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Though his ministry follows mine, I\u2019m not even worthy to be
        his slave and untie the straps of his sandal.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: Jesus, the Lamb of God'
      title: Jesus, the Lamb of God
      number: 28
      content: 'This encounter took place in Bethany, an area east of the Jordan
        River, where John was baptizing.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "The next day John saw Jesus coming toward him and said, \u201CLook!
        The Lamb of God who takes away the sin of the world! "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "He is the one I was talking about when I said, \u2018A man is coming
        after me who is far greater than I am, for he existed long before me.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "I did not recognize him as the Messiah, but I have been baptizing
        with water so that he might be revealed to Israel.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "Then John testified, \u201CI saw the Holy Spirit descending like
        a dove from heaven and resting upon him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "I didn\u2019t know he was the one, but when God sent me to baptize
        with water, he told me, \u2018The one on whom you see the Spirit descend
        and rest is the one who will baptize with the Holy Spirit.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: The First Disciples'
      title: The First Disciples
      number: 34
      content: "I saw this happen to Jesus, so I testify that he is the Chosen One
        of God.[[COMMENT(0)]]\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '1:34 '
        content: Some manuscripts read <b>the Son of God.</b>
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'The following day John was again standing with two of his disciples. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "As Jesus walked by, John looked at him and declared, \u201CLook!
        There is the Lamb of God!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "When John\u2019s two disciples heard this, they followed Jesus.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "Jesus looked around and saw them following. <JESUS>\u201CWhat do
        you want?\u201D </JESUS>he asked them.They replied, \u201CRabbi\u201D (which
        means \u201CTeacher\u201D), \u201Cwhere are you staying?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CCome and see,\u201D </JESUS>he said. It was about
        four o\u2019clock in the afternoon when they went with him to the place where
        he was staying, and they remained with him the rest of the day.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "Andrew, Simon Peter\u2019s brother, was one of these men who heard
        what John said and then followed Jesus. "
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: "Andrew went to find his brother, Simon, and told him, \u201CWe have
        found the Messiah\u201D (which means \u201CChrist\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]).  "
      comments:
      - number: '1:41 '
        content: "<b>Messiah </b>(a Hebrew term) and <b>Christ </b>(a Greek term)
          both mean \u201Canointed one.\u201D"
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: "Then Andrew brought Simon to meet Jesus. Looking intently at Simon,
        Jesus said, <JESUS>\u201CYour name is Simon, son of John\u2014but you will
        be called Cephas\u201D</JESUS> (which means \u201CPeter\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]).  "
      comments:
      - number: '1:42 '
        content: "The names <b>Cephas </b>(from Aramaic) and <b>Peter </b>(from Greek)
          both mean \u201Crock.\u201D"
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: "The next day Jesus decided to go to Galilee. He found Philip and
        said to him, <JESUS>\u201CCome, follow me.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: "Philip was from Bethsaida, Andrew and Peter\u2019s hometown.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: "Philip went to look for Nathanael and told him, \u201CWe have found
        the very person Moses[[COMMENT(0)]] and the prophets wrote about! His name
        is Jesus, the son of Joseph from Nazareth.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '1:45 '
        content: Greek <b>Moses in the law.</b>
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: "\u201CNazareth!\u201D exclaimed Nathanael. \u201CCan anything good
        come from Nazareth?\u201D\u201CCome and see for yourself,\u201D Philip replied.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: "As they approached, Jesus said, <JESUS>\u201CNow here is a genuine
        son of Israel\u2014a man of complete integrity.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: "\u201CHow do you know about me?\u201D Nathanael asked.Jesus replied,
        <JESUS>\u201CI could see you under the fig tree before Philip found you.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: "Then Nathanael exclaimed, \u201CRabbi, you are the Son of God\u2014the
        King of Israel!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: "Jesus asked him, <JESUS>\u201CDo you believe this just because I
        told you I had seen you under the fig tree? You will see greater things than
        this.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: "Then he said, <JESUS>\u201CI tell you the truth, you will all see
        heaven open and the angels of God going up and down on the Son of Man, the
        one who is the stairway between heaven and earth.</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]]<JESUS>\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments:
      - number: '1:51 '
        content: "Greek <b>going up and down on the Son of Man; </b>see Gen 28:10-17.
          \u201CSon of Man\u201D is a title Jesus used for himself."
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Wedding at Cana'
      title: The Wedding at Cana
      number: 1
      content: "  The next day[[COMMENT(0)]] there was a wedding celebration in the
        village of Cana in Galilee. Jesus\u2019 mother was there, "
      comments:
      - number: '2:1 '
        content: Greek <b>On the third day; </b>see 1:35, 43.
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'and Jesus and his disciples were also invited to the celebration. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "The wine supply ran out during the festivities, so Jesus\u2019 mother
        told him, \u201CThey have no more wine.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CDear woman, that\u2019s not our problem,\u201D </JESUS>Jesus
        replied. <JESUS>\u201CMy time has not yet come.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "But his mother told the servants, \u201CDo whatever he tells you.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Standing nearby were six stone water jars, used for Jewish ceremonial
        washing. Each could hold twenty to thirty gallons.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '2:6 '
        content: Greek <b>2 or 3 measures </b>[75 to 113 liters].
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Jesus told the servants, <JESUS>\u201CFill the jars with water.\u201D</JESUS>
        When the jars had been filled, "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "he said, <JESUS>\u201CNow dip some out, and take it to the master
        of ceremonies.\u201D</JESUS> So the servants followed his instructions.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'When the master of ceremonies tasted the water that was now wine,
        not knowing where it had come from (though, of course, the servants knew),
        he called the bridegroom over. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CA host always serves the best wine first,\u201D he said. \u201CThen,
        when everyone has had a lot to drink, he brings out the less expensive wine.
        But you have kept the best until now!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'This miraculous sign at Cana in Galilee was the first time Jesus
        revealed his glory. And his disciples believed in him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: Jesus Clears the Temple'
      title: Jesus Clears the Temple
      number: 12
      content: 'After the wedding he went to Capernaum for a few days with his mother,
        his brothers, and his disciples.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'It was nearly time for the Jewish Passover celebration, so Jesus
        went to Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'In the Temple area he saw merchants selling cattle, sheep, and doves
        for sacrifices; he also saw dealers at tables exchanging foreign money. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Jesus made a whip from some ropes and chased them all out of the
        Temple. He drove out the sheep and cattle, scattered the money changers\u2019
        coins over the floor, and turned over their tables. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Then, going over to the people who sold doves, he told them, <JESUS>\u201CGet
        these things out of here. Stop turning my Father\u2019s house into a marketplace!\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Then his disciples remembered this prophecy from the Scriptures:
        \u201CPassion for God\u2019s house will consume me.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '2:17 '
        content: "Or <b>\u201CConcern for God\u2019s house will be my undoing.\u201D
          </b>Ps 69:9."
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "But the Jewish leaders demanded, \u201CWhat are you doing? If God
        gave you authority to do this, show us a miraculous sign to prove it.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CAll right,\u201D </JESUS>Jesus replied. <JESUS>\u201CDestroy
        this temple, and in three days I will raise it up.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "\u201CWhat!\u201D they exclaimed. \u201CIt has taken forty-six years
        to build this Temple, and you can rebuild it in three days?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "But when Jesus said \u201Cthis temple,\u201D he meant his own body. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: Jesus and Nicodemus'
      title: Jesus and Nicodemus
      number: 22
      content: 'After he was raised from the dead, his disciples remembered he had
        said this, and they believed both the Scriptures and what Jesus had said.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Because of the miraculous signs Jesus did in Jerusalem at the Passover
        celebration, many began to trust in him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "But Jesus didn\u2019t trust them, because he knew all about people. "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "No one needed to tell him about human nature, for he knew what was
        in each person\u2019s heart."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: '  There was a man named Nicodemus, a Jewish religious leader who
        was a Pharisee. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "After dark one evening, he came to speak with Jesus. \u201CRabbi,\u201D
        he said, \u201Cwe all know that God has sent you to teach us. Your miraculous
        signs are evidence that God is with you.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Jesus replied, <JESUS>\u201CI tell you the truth, unless you are
        born again,</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>you cannot see the Kingdom of God.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: '3:3 '
        content: Or <b>born from above; </b>also in 3:7.
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CWhat do you mean?\u201D exclaimed Nicodemus. \u201CHow can
        an old man go back into his mother\u2019s womb and be born again?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Jesus replied, <JESUS>\u201CI assure you, no one can enter the Kingdom
        of God without being born of water and the Spirit.</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '3:5 '
        content: Or <b>and spirit. </b>The Greek word for <b>Spirit </b>can also
          be translated <b>wind; </b>see 3:8.
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: '<JESUS>Humans can reproduce only human life, but the Holy Spirit
        gives birth to spiritual life.</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '3:6 '
        content: Greek <b>what is born of the Spirit is spirit.</b>
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "<JESUS>So don\u2019t be surprised when I say, \u2018You</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]] 
        <JESUS>must be born again.\u2019</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: '3:7 '
        content: The Greek word for <b>you </b>is plural; also in 3:12.
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "<JESUS>The wind blows wherever it wants. Just as you can hear the
        wind but can\u2019t tell where it comes from or where it is going, so you
        can\u2019t explain how people are born of the Spirit.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CHow are these things possible?\u201D Nicodemus asked.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Jesus replied, <JESUS>\u201CYou are a respected Jewish teacher, and
        yet you don\u2019t understand these things?</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "<JESUS>I assure you, we tell you what we know and have seen, and
        yet you won\u2019t believe our testimony.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "<JESUS>But if you don\u2019t believe me when I tell you about earthly
        things, how can you possibly believe if I tell you about heavenly things?</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: '<JESUS>No one has ever gone to heaven and returned. But the Son of
        Man</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>has come down from heaven.</JESUS>  '
      comments:
      - number: '3:13 '
        content: "Some manuscripts add <b>who lives in heaven. </b>\u201CSon of Man\u201D
          is a title Jesus used for himself."
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: '<JESUS>And as Moses lifted up the bronze snake on a pole in the wilderness,
        so the Son of Man must be lifted up,</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: '<JESUS>so that everyone who believes in him will have eternal life.</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '3:15 '
        content: 'Or <b>everyone who believes will have eternal life in him.</b>  '
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CFor this is how God loved the world: He gave</JESUS> 
        [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>his one and only Son, so that everyone who believes
        in him will not perish but have eternal life.</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: '3:16 '
        content: '  Or   <b>For God loved the world so much that he gave.</b>  '
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: '<JESUS>God sent his Son into the world not to judge the world, but
        to save the world through him.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CThere is no judgment against anyone who believes in
        him. But anyone who does not believe in him has already been judged for not
        believing in God\u2019s one and only Son.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "<JESUS>And the judgment is based on this fact: God\u2019s light came
        into the world, but people loved the darkness more than the light, for their
        actions were evil.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: '<JESUS>All who do evil hate the light and refuse to go near it for
        fear their sins will be exposed.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: John the Baptist Exalts Jesus'
      title: John the Baptist Exalts Jesus
      number: 21
      content: "<JESUS>But those who do what is right come to the light so others
        can see that they are doing what God wants.</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]]<JESUS>\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: '3:21 '
        content: Or <b>can see God at work in what he is doing.</b>
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Then Jesus and his disciples left Jerusalem and went into the Judean
        countryside. Jesus spent some time with them there, baptizing people.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'At this time John the Baptist was baptizing at Aenon, near Salim,
        because there was plenty of water there; and people kept coming to him for
        baptism. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: '(This was before John was thrown into prison.) '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "A debate broke out between John\u2019s disciples and a certain Jew[[COMMENT(0)]]
        over ceremonial cleansing. "
      comments:
      - number: '3:25 '
        content: Some manuscripts read <b>some Jews.</b>
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "So John\u2019s disciples came to him and said, \u201CRabbi, the man
        you met on the other side of the Jordan River, the one you identified as
        the Messiah, is also baptizing people. And everybody is going to him instead
        of coming to us.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "John replied, \u201CNo one can receive anything unless God gives
        it from heaven. "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "You yourselves know how plainly I told you, \u2018I am not the Messiah.
        I am only here to prepare the way for him.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "It is the bridegroom who marries the bride, and the bridegroom\u2019s
        friend is simply glad to stand with him and hear his vows. Therefore, I am
        filled with joy at his success. "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'He must become greater and greater, and I must become less and less.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "\u201CHe has come from above and is greater than anyone else. We
        are of the earth, and we speak of earthly things, but he has come from heaven
        and is greater than anyone else.[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '3:31 '
        content: Some manuscripts do not include <b>and is greater than anyone else.</b>
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'He testifies about what he has seen and heard, but how few believe
        what he tells them! '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'Anyone who accepts his testimony can affirm that God is true. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "For he is sent by God. He speaks God\u2019s words, for God gives
        him the Spirit without limit. "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'The Father loves his Son and has put everything into his hands. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "And anyone who believes in God\u2019s Son has eternal life. Anyone
        who doesn\u2019t obey the Son will never experience eternal life but remains
        under God\u2019s angry judgment.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jesus and the Samaritan Woman'
      title: Jesus and the Samaritan Woman
      number: 1
      content: '  Jesus[[COMMENT(0)]] knew the Pharisees had heard that he was baptizing
        and making more disciples than John '
      comments:
      - number: '4:1 '
        content: Some manuscripts read <b>The Lord.</b>
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "(though Jesus himself didn\u2019t baptize them\u2014his disciples
        did). "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'So he left Judea and returned to Galilee.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'He had to go through Samaria on the way. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Eventually he came to the Samaritan village of Sychar, near the field
        that Jacob gave to his son Joseph. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Jacob\u2019s well was there; and Jesus, tired from the long walk,
        sat wearily beside the well about noontime. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Soon a Samaritan woman came to draw water, and Jesus said to her,
        <JESUS>\u201CPlease give me a drink.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'He was alone at the time because his disciples had gone into the
        village to buy some food.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "The woman was surprised, for Jews refuse to have anything to do with
        Samaritans.[[COMMENT(0)]] She said to Jesus, \u201CYou are a Jew, and I am
        a Samaritan woman. Why are you asking me for a drink?\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '4:9 '
        content: Some manuscripts do not include this sentence.
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Jesus replied, <JESUS>\u201CIf you only knew the gift God has for
        you and who you are speaking to, you would ask me, and I would give you living
        water.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CBut sir, you don\u2019t have a rope or a bucket,\u201D she
        said, \u201Cand this well is very deep. Where would you get this living water? "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And besides, do you think you\u2019re greater than our ancestor Jacob,
        who gave us this well? How can you offer better water than he and his sons
        and his animals enjoyed?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Jesus replied, <JESUS>\u201CAnyone who drinks this water will soon
        become thirsty again.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "<JESUS>But those who drink the water I give will never be thirsty
        again. It becomes a fresh, bubbling spring within them, giving them eternal
        life.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u201CPlease, sir,\u201D the woman said, \u201Cgive me this water!
        Then I\u2019ll never be thirsty again, and I won\u2019t have to come here
        to get water.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CGo and get your husband,\u201D </JESUS>Jesus told
        her.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u201CI don\u2019t have a husband,\u201D the woman replied.Jesus
        said, <JESUS>\u201CYou\u2019re right! You don\u2019t have a husband\u2014</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "<JESUS>for you have had five husbands, and you aren\u2019t even married
        to the man you\u2019re living with now. You certainly spoke the truth!\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "\u201CSir,\u201D the woman said, \u201Cyou must be a prophet. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "So tell me, why is it that you Jews insist that Jerusalem is the
        only place of worship, while we Samaritans claim it is here at Mount Gerizim,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        where our ancestors worshiped?\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '4:20 '
        content: Greek <b>on this mountain.</b>
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Jesus replied, <JESUS>\u201CBelieve me, dear woman, the time is coming
        when it will no longer matter whether you worship the Father on this mountain
        or in Jerusalem.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: '<JESUS>You Samaritans know very little about the one you worship,
        while we Jews know all about him, for salvation comes through the Jews.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "<JESUS>But the time is coming\u2014indeed it\u2019s here now\u2014when
        true worshipers will worship the Father in spirit and in truth. The Father
        is looking for those who will worship him that way.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "<JESUS>For God is Spirit, so those who worship him must worship in
        spirit and in truth.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "The woman said, \u201CI know the Messiah is coming\u2014the one who
        is called Christ. When he comes, he will explain everything to us.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Then Jesus told her, <JESUS>\u201C</JESUS><smallcaps>I Am</smallcaps>
        the Messiah!\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]<smallcaps>or </smallcaps><smallcaps>Greek
        reads </smallcaps>  "
      comments:
      - number: '4:26 '
        content: "Or <b>\u201CThe \u2018<span class=\"ChapterContent_nd__ECPAf\">I
          Am</span>\u2019 is here\u201D; </b><b>\u201CI am the <span class=\"ChapterContent_nd__ECPAf\">Lord</span>\u201D;
          </b><b>\u201CI am, the one speaking to you.\u201D </b>See Exod 3:14."
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Just then his disciples came back. They were shocked to find him
        talking to a woman, but none of them had the nerve to ask, \u201CWhat do
        you want with her?\u201D or \u201CWhy are you talking to her?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'The woman left her water jar beside the well and ran back to the
        village, telling everyone, '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "\u201CCome and see a man who told me everything I ever did! Could
        he possibly be the Messiah?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'So the people came streaming from the village to see him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Meanwhile, the disciples were urging Jesus, \u201CRabbi, eat something.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "But Jesus replied, <JESUS>\u201CI have a kind of food you know nothing
        about.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "\u201CDid someone bring him food while we were gone?\u201D the disciples
        asked each other.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "Then Jesus explained: <JESUS>\u201CMy nourishment comes from doing
        the will of God, who sent me, and from finishing his work.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "<JESUS>You know the saying, \u2018Four months between planting and
        harvest.\u2019 But I say, wake up and look around. The fields are already
        ripe</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>for harvest.</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: '4:35 '
        content: Greek <b>white.</b>
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: '<JESUS>The harvesters are paid good wages, and the fruit they harvest
        is people brought to eternal life. What joy awaits both the planter and the
        harvester alike!</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "<JESUS>You know the saying, \u2018One plants and another harvests.\u2019
        And it\u2019s true.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: Many Samaritans Believe'
      title: Many Samaritans Believe
      number: 38
      content: "<JESUS>I sent you to harvest where you didn\u2019t plant; others
        had already done the work, and now you will get to gather the harvest.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "Many Samaritans from the village believed in Jesus because the woman
        had said, \u201CHe told me everything I ever did!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'When they came out to see him, they begged him to stay in their village.
        So he stayed for two days, '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'long enough for many more to hear his message and believe. '
      comments: []
    - name: "42: Jesus Heals an Official\u2019s Son"
      title: "Jesus Heals an Official\u2019s Son"
      number: 42
      content: "Then they said to the woman, \u201CNow we believe, not just because
        of what you told us, but because we have heard him ourselves. Now we know
        that he is indeed the Savior of the world.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'At the end of the two days, Jesus went on to Galilee. '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: 'He himself had said that a prophet is not honored in his own hometown. '
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: 'Yet the Galileans welcomed him, for they had been in Jerusalem at
        the Passover celebration and had seen everything he did there.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: 'As he traveled through Galilee, he came to Cana, where he had turned
        the water into wine. There was a government official in nearby Capernaum
        whose son was very sick. '
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: 'When he heard that Jesus had come from Judea to Galilee, he went
        and begged Jesus to come to Capernaum to heal his son, who was about to die.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: "Jesus asked, <JESUS>\u201CWill you never believe in me unless you
        see miraculous signs and wonders?\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: "The official pleaded, \u201CLord, please come now before my little
        boy dies.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: "Then Jesus told him, <JESUS>\u201CGo back home. Your son will live!\u201D</JESUS>
        And the man believed what Jesus said and started home.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: 'While the man was on his way, some of his servants met him with the
        news that his son was alive and well. '
      comments: []
    - name: '52: '
      title: 
      number: 52
      content: "He asked them when the boy had begun to get better, and they replied,
        \u201CYesterday afternoon at one o\u2019clock his fever suddenly disappeared!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '53: '
      title: 
      number: 53
      content: "Then the father realized that that was the very time Jesus had told
        him, <JESUS>\u201CYour son will live.\u201D</JESUS> And he and his entire
        household believed in Jesus. "
      comments: []
    - name: '54: '
      title: 
      number: 54
      content: This was the second miraculous sign Jesus did in Galilee after coming
        from Judea.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jesus Heals a Lame Man'
      title: Jesus Heals a Lame Man
      number: 1
      content: '  Afterward Jesus returned to Jerusalem for one of the Jewish holy
        days. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Inside the city, near the Sheep Gate, was the pool of Bethesda,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        with five covered porches. '
      comments:
      - number: '5:2 '
        content: Other manuscripts read <b>Beth-zatha; </b>still others read <b>Bethsaida.</b>
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Crowds of sick people\u2014blind, lame, or paralyzed\u2014lay on
        the porches.[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '5:3 '
        content: 'Some manuscripts add an expanded conclusion to verse 3 and all
          of verse 4: <b>waiting for a certain movement of the water, </b><b>for
          an angel of the Lord came from time to time and stirred up the water. And
          the first person to step in after the water was stirred was healed of whatever
          disease he had.</b>'
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'One of the men lying there had been sick for thirty-eight years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "When Jesus saw him and knew he had been ill for a long time, he asked
        him, <JESUS>\u201CWould you like to get well?\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CI can\u2019t, sir,\u201D the sick man said, \u201Cfor I have
        no one to put me into the pool when the water bubbles up. Someone else always
        gets there ahead of me.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Jesus told him, <JESUS>\u201CStand up, pick up your mat, and walk!\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Instantly, the man was healed! He rolled up his sleeping mat and
        began walking! But this miracle happened on the Sabbath, '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "so the Jewish leaders objected. They said to the man who was cured,
        \u201CYou can\u2019t work on the Sabbath! The law doesn\u2019t allow you
        to carry that sleeping mat!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "But he replied, \u201CThe man who healed me told me, \u2018Pick up
        your mat and walk.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CWho said such a thing as that?\u201D they demanded.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "The man didn\u2019t know, for Jesus had disappeared into the crowd. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "But afterward Jesus found him in the Temple and told him, <JESUS>\u201CNow
        you are well; so stop sinning, or something even worse may happen to you.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: Jesus Claims to Be the Son of God'
      title: Jesus Claims to Be the Son of God
      number: 15
      content: 'Then the man went and told the Jewish leaders that it was Jesus who
        had healed him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'So the Jewish leaders began harassing[[COMMENT(0)]] Jesus for breaking
        the Sabbath rules. '
      comments:
      - number: '5:16 '
        content: Or <b>persecuting.</b>
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "But Jesus replied, <JESUS>\u201CMy Father is always working, and
        so am I.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'So the Jewish leaders tried all the harder to find a way to kill
        him. For he not only broke the Sabbath, he called God his Father, thereby
        making himself equal with God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "So Jesus explained, <JESUS>\u201CI tell you the truth, the Son can
        do nothing by himself. He does only what he sees the Father doing. Whatever
        the Father does, the Son also does.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: '<JESUS>For the Father loves the Son and shows him everything he is
        doing. In fact, the Father will show him how to do even greater works than
        healing this man. Then you will truly be astonished.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: '<JESUS>For just as the Father gives life to those he raises from
        the dead, so the Son gives life to anyone he wants.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: '<JESUS>In addition, the Father judges no one. Instead, he has given
        the Son absolute authority to judge,</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: '<JESUS>so that everyone will honor the Son, just as they honor the
        Father. Anyone who does not honor the Son is certainly not honoring the Father
        who sent him.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CI tell you the truth, those who listen to my message
        and believe in God who sent me have eternal life. They will never be condemned
        for their sins, but they have already passed from death into life.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CAnd I assure you that the time is coming, indeed it\u2019s
        here now, when the dead will hear my voice\u2014the voice of the Son of God.
        And those who listen will live.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: '<JESUS>The Father has life in himself, and he has granted that same
        life-giving power to his Son.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: '<JESUS>And he has given him authority to judge everyone because he
        is the Son of Man.</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '5:27 '
        content: "\u201CSon of Man\u201D is a title Jesus used for himself."
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "<JESUS>Don\u2019t be so surprised! Indeed, the time is coming when
        all the dead in their graves will hear the voice of God\u2019s Son,</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: '<JESUS>and they will rise again. Those who have done good will rise
        to experience eternal life, and those who have continued in evil will rise
        to experience judgment.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: Witnesses to Jesus'
      title: Witnesses to Jesus
      number: 30
      content: '<JESUS>I can do nothing on my own. I judge as God tells me. Therefore,
        my judgment is just, because I carry out the will of the one who sent me,
        not my own will.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CIf I were to testify on my own behalf, my testimony
        would not be valid.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: '<JESUS>But someone else is also testifying about me, and I assure
        you that everything he says about me is true.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: '<JESUS>In fact, you sent investigators to listen to John the Baptist,
        and his testimony about me was true.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: '<JESUS>Of course, I have no need of human witnesses, but I say these
        things so you might be saved.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: '<JESUS>John was like a burning and shining lamp, and you were excited
        for a while about his message.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "<JESUS>But I have a greater witness than John\u2014my teachings and
        my miracles. The Father gave me these works to accomplish, and they prove
        that he sent me.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: '<JESUS>And the Father who sent me has testified about me himself.
        You have never heard his voice or seen him face to face,</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "<JESUS>and you do not have his message in your hearts, because you
        do not believe me\u2014the one he sent to you.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CYou search the Scriptures because you think they give
        you eternal life. But the Scriptures point to me!</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: '<JESUS>Yet you refuse to come to me to receive this life.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CYour approval means nothing to me,</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: "<JESUS>because I know you don\u2019t have God\u2019s love within
        you.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: "<JESUS>For I have come to you in my Father\u2019s name, and you have
        rejected me. Yet if others come in their own name, you gladly welcome them.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: "<JESUS>No wonder you can\u2019t believe! For you gladly honor each
        other, but you don\u2019t care about the honor that comes from the one who
        alone is God.</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '5:44 '
        content: Some manuscripts read <b>from the only One.</b>
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CYet it isn\u2019t I who will accuse you before the
        Father. Moses will accuse you! Yes, Moses, in whom you put your hopes.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: '<JESUS>If you really believed Moses, you would believe me, because
        he wrote about me.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: "<JESUS>But since you don\u2019t believe what he wrote, how will you
        believe what I say?\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jesus Feeds Five Thousand'
      title: Jesus Feeds Five Thousand
      number: 1
      content: '  After this, Jesus crossed over to the far side of the Sea of Galilee,
        also known as the Sea of Tiberias. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'A huge crowd kept following him wherever he went, because they saw
        his miraculous signs as he healed the sick. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Then Jesus climbed a hill and sat down with his disciples around
        him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: '(It was nearly time for the Jewish Passover celebration.) '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Jesus soon saw a huge crowd of people coming to look for him. Turning
        to Philip, he asked, <JESUS>\u201CWhere can we buy bread to feed all these
        people?\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'He was testing Philip, for he already knew what he was going to do.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Philip replied, \u201CEven if we worked for months, we wouldn\u2019t
        have enough money[[COMMENT(0)]] to feed them!\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '6:7 '
        content: "Greek <b>Two hundred denarii would not be enough. </b>A denarius
          was equivalent to a laborer\u2019s full day\u2019s wage."
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Then Andrew, Simon Peter\u2019s brother, spoke up. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CThere\u2019s a young boy here with five barley loaves and two
        fish. But what good is that with this huge crowd?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CTell everyone to sit down,\u201D </JESUS>Jesus said.
        So they all sat down on the grassy slopes. (The men alone numbered about
        5,000.) "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Then Jesus took the loaves, gave thanks to God, and distributed them
        to the people. Afterward he did the same with the fish. And they all ate
        as much as they wanted. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "After everyone was full, Jesus told his disciples, <JESUS>\u201CNow
        gather the leftovers, so that nothing is wasted.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'So they picked up the pieces and filled twelve baskets with scraps
        left by the people who had eaten from the five barley loaves.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "When the people saw him[[COMMENT(0)]] do this miraculous sign, they
        exclaimed, \u201CSurely, he is the Prophet we have been expecting!\u201D[[COMMENT(1)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '6:14a '
        content: Some manuscripts read <b>Jesus.</b>
      - number: '6:14b '
        content: See Deut 18:15, 18; Mal 4:5-6.
    - name: '15: Jesus Walks on Water'
      title: Jesus Walks on Water
      number: 15
      content: 'When Jesus saw that they were ready to force him to be their king,
        he slipped away into the hills by himself.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "That evening Jesus\u2019 disciples went down to the shore to wait
        for him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "But as darkness fell and Jesus still hadn\u2019t come back, they
        got into the boat and headed across the lake toward Capernaum. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Soon a gale swept down upon them, and the sea grew very rough. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'They had rowed three or four miles[[COMMENT(0)]] when suddenly they
        saw Jesus walking on the water toward the boat. They were terrified, '
      comments:
      - number: '6:19 '
        content: Greek <b>25 or 30 stadia </b>[4.6 or 5.5 kilometers].
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "but he called out to them, <JESUS>\u201CDon\u2019t be afraid. I am
        here!</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]]<smallcaps>Greek reads </smallcaps><JESUS>\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: '6:20 '
        content: "Or <b>The \u2018<span class=\"ChapterContent_nd__ECPAf\">I Am</span>\u2019
          is here; </b><b>I am. </b>See Exod 3:14."
    - name: '21: Jesus, the Bread of Life'
      title: Jesus, the Bread of Life
      number: 21
      content: 'Then they were eager to let him in the boat, and immediately they
        arrived at their destination!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'The next day the crowd that had stayed on the far shore saw that
        the disciples had taken the only boat, and they realized Jesus had not gone
        with them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Several boats from Tiberias landed near the place where the Lord
        had blessed the bread and the people had eaten. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'So when the crowd saw that neither Jesus nor his disciples were there,
        they got into the boats and went across to Capernaum to look for him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "They found him on the other side of the lake and asked, \u201CRabbi,
        when did you get here?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Jesus replied, <JESUS>\u201CI tell you the truth, you want to be
        with me because I fed you, not because you understood the miraculous signs.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "<JESUS>But don\u2019t be so concerned about perishable things like
        food. Spend your energy seeking the eternal life that the Son of Man</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]] 
        <JESUS>can give you. For God the Father has given me the seal of his approval.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: '6:27 '
        content: "\u201CSon of Man\u201D is a title Jesus used for himself."
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "They replied, \u201CWe want to perform God\u2019s works, too. What
        should we do?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Jesus told them, <JESUS>\u201CThis is the only work God wants from
        you: Believe in the one he has sent.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "They answered, \u201CShow us a miraculous sign if you want us to
        believe in you. What can you do? "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "After all, our ancestors ate manna while they journeyed through the
        wilderness! The Scriptures say, \u2018Moses gave them bread from heaven to
        eat.\u2019[[COMMENT(0)]]\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '6:31 '
        content: Exod 16:4; Ps 78:24.
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "Jesus said, <JESUS>\u201CI tell you the truth, Moses didn\u2019t
        give you bread from heaven. My Father did. And now he offers you the true
        bread from heaven.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "<JESUS>The true bread of God is the one who comes down from heaven
        and gives life to the world.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "\u201CSir,\u201D they said, \u201Cgive us that bread every day.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "Jesus replied, <JESUS>\u201CI am the bread of life. Whoever comes
        to me will never be hungry again. Whoever believes in me will never be thirsty.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "<JESUS>But you haven\u2019t believed in me even though you have seen
        me.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: '<JESUS>However, those the Father has given me will come to me, and
        I will never reject them.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: '<JESUS>For I have come down from heaven to do the will of God who
        sent me, not to do my own will.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: '<JESUS>And this is the will of God, that I should not lose even one
        of all those he has given me, but that I should raise them up at the last
        day.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "<JESUS>For it is my Father\u2019s will that all who see his Son and
        believe in him should have eternal life. I will raise them up at the last
        day.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: "Then the people[[COMMENT(0)]] began to murmur in disagreement because
        he had said, <JESUS>\u201CI am the bread that came down from heaven.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: '6:41 '
        content: Greek <b>Jewish people; </b>also in 6:52.
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: "They said, \u201CIsn\u2019t this Jesus, the son of Joseph? We know
        his father and mother. How can he say, \u2018I came down from heaven\u2019?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: "But Jesus replied, <JESUS>\u201CStop complaining about what I said.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: '<JESUS>For no one can come to me unless the Father who sent me draws
        them to me, and at the last day I will raise them up.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: "<JESUS>As it is written in the Scriptures,</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]] 
        <JESUS>\u2018They will all be taught by God.\u2019 Everyone who listens to
        the Father and learns from him comes to me.</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: '6:45 '
        content: Greek <b>in the prophets. </b>Isa 54:13.
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: '<JESUS>(Not that anyone has ever seen the Father; only I, who was
        sent from God, have seen him.)</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CI tell you the truth, anyone who believes has eternal
        life.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: '<JESUS>Yes, I am the bread of life!</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: '<JESUS>Your ancestors ate manna in the wilderness, but they all died.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: '<JESUS>Anyone who eats the bread from heaven, however, will never
        die.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: "<JESUS>I am the living bread that came down from heaven. Anyone who
        eats this bread will live forever; and this bread, which I will offer so
        the world may live, is my flesh.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '52: '
      title: 
      number: 52
      content: "Then the people began arguing with each other about what he meant.
        \u201CHow can this man give us his flesh to eat?\u201D they asked.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '53: '
      title: 
      number: 53
      content: "So Jesus said again, <JESUS>\u201CI tell you the truth, unless you
        eat the flesh of the Son of Man and drink his blood, you cannot have eternal
        life within you.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '54: '
      title: 
      number: 54
      content: '<JESUS>But anyone who eats my flesh and drinks my blood has eternal
        life, and I will raise that person at the last day.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '55: '
      title: 
      number: 55
      content: '<JESUS>For my flesh is true food, and my blood is true drink.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '56: '
      title: 
      number: 56
      content: '<JESUS>Anyone who eats my flesh and drinks my blood remains in me,
        and I in him.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '57: '
      title: 
      number: 57
      content: '<JESUS>I live because of the living Father who sent me; in the same
        way, anyone who feeds on me will live because of me.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '58: '
      title: 
      number: 58
      content: "<JESUS>I am the true bread that came down from heaven. Anyone who
        eats this bread will not die as your ancestors did (even though they ate
        the manna) but will live forever.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '59: Many Disciples Desert Jesus'
      title: Many Disciples Desert Jesus
      number: 59
      content: 'He said these things while he was teaching in the synagogue in Capernaum.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '60: '
      title: 
      number: 60
      content: "Many of his disciples said, \u201CThis is very hard to understand.
        How can anyone accept it?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '61: '
      title: 
      number: 61
      content: "Jesus was aware that his disciples were complaining, so he said to
        them, <JESUS>\u201CDoes this offend you?</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '62: '
      title: 
      number: 62
      content: '<JESUS>Then what will you think if you see the Son of Man ascend
        to heaven again?</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '63: '
      title: 
      number: 63
      content: '<JESUS>The Spirit alone gives eternal life. Human effort accomplishes
        nothing. And the very words I have spoken to you are spirit and life.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '64: '
      title: 
      number: 64
      content: "<JESUS>But some of you do not believe me.\u201D</JESUS> (For Jesus
        knew from the beginning which ones didn\u2019t believe, and he knew who would
        betray him.) "
      comments: []
    - name: '65: '
      title: 
      number: 65
      content: "Then he said, <JESUS>\u201CThat is why I said that people can\u2019t
        come to me unless the Father gives them to me.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '66: '
      title: 
      number: 66
      content: 'At this point many of his disciples turned away and deserted him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '67: '
      title: 
      number: 67
      content: "Then Jesus turned to the Twelve and asked, <JESUS>\u201CAre you also
        going to leave?\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '68: '
      title: 
      number: 68
      content: "Simon Peter replied, \u201CLord, to whom would we go? You have the
        words that give eternal life. "
      comments: []
    - name: '69: '
      title: 
      number: 69
      content: "We believe, and we know you are the Holy One of God.[[COMMENT(0)]]\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '6:69 '
        content: Other manuscripts read <b>you are the Christ, the Holy One of God;
          </b>still others read <b>you are the Christ, the Son of God; </b>and still
          others read <b>you are the Christ, the Son of the living God.</b>
    - name: '70: '
      title: 
      number: 70
      content: "Then Jesus said, <JESUS>\u201CI chose the twelve of you, but one
        is a devil.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '71: '
      title: 
      number: 71
      content: He was speaking of Judas, son of Simon Iscariot, one of the Twelve,
        who would later betray him.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jesus and His Brothers'
      title: Jesus and His Brothers
      number: 1
      content: '  After this, Jesus traveled around Galilee. He wanted to stay out
        of Judea, where the Jewish leaders were plotting his death. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'But soon it was time for the Jewish Festival of Shelters, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "and Jesus\u2019 brothers said to him, \u201CLeave here and go to
        Judea, where your followers can see your miracles! "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "You can\u2019t become famous if you hide like this! If you can do
        such wonderful things, show yourself to the world!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "For even his brothers didn\u2019t believe in him.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Jesus replied, <JESUS>\u201CNow is not the right time for me to go,
        but you can go anytime.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "<JESUS>The world can\u2019t hate you, but it does hate me because
        I accuse it of doing evil.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "<JESUS>You go on. I\u2019m not going</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>to
        this festival, because my time has not yet come.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: '7:8 '
        content: Some manuscripts read <b>not yet going.</b>
    - name: '9: Jesus Teaches Openly at the Temple'
      title: Jesus Teaches Openly at the Temple
      number: 9
      content: 'After saying these things, Jesus remained in Galilee.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'But after his brothers left for the festival, Jesus also went, though
        secretly, staying out of public view. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'The Jewish leaders tried to find him at the festival and kept asking
        if anyone had seen him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "There was a lot of grumbling about him among the crowds. Some argued,
        \u201CHe\u2019s a good man,\u201D but others said, \u201CHe\u2019s nothing
        but a fraud who deceives the people.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'But no one had the courage to speak favorably about him in public,
        for they were afraid of getting in trouble with the Jewish leaders.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Then, midway through the festival, Jesus went up to the Temple and
        began to teach. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "The people[[COMMENT(0)]] were surprised when they heard him. \u201CHow
        does he know so much when he hasn\u2019t been trained?\u201D they asked.  "
      comments:
      - number: '7:15 '
        content: Greek <b>Jewish people.</b>
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "So Jesus told them, <JESUS>\u201CMy message is not my own; it comes
        from God who sent me.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: '<JESUS>Anyone who wants to do the will of God will know whether my
        teaching is from God or is merely my own.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: '<JESUS>Those who speak for themselves want glory only for themselves,
        but a person who seeks to honor the one who sent him speaks truth, not lies.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "<JESUS>Moses gave you the law, but none of you obeys it! In fact,
        you are trying to kill me.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "The crowd replied, \u201CYou\u2019re demon possessed! Who\u2019s
        trying to kill you?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Jesus replied, <JESUS>\u201CI did one miracle on the Sabbath, and
        you were amazed.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "<JESUS>But you work on the Sabbath, too, when you obey Moses\u2019
        law of circumcision. (Actually, this tradition of circumcision began with
        the patriarchs, long before the law of Moses.)</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: '<JESUS>For if the correct time for circumcising your son falls on
        the Sabbath, you go ahead and do it so as not to break the law of Moses.
        So why should you be angry with me for healing a man on the Sabbath?</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: Is Jesus the Messiah?'
      title: Is Jesus the Messiah?
      number: 24
      content: "<JESUS>Look beneath the surface so you can judge correctly.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Some of the people who lived in Jerusalem started to ask each other,
        \u201CIsn\u2019t this the man they are trying to kill? "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'But here he is, speaking in public, and they say nothing to him.
        Could our leaders possibly believe that he is the Messiah? '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "But how could he be? For we know where this man comes from. When
        the Messiah comes, he will simply appear; no one will know where he comes
        from.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "While Jesus was teaching in the Temple, he called out, <JESUS>\u201CYes,
        you know me, and you know where I come from. But I\u2019m not here on my
        own. The one who sent me is true, and you don\u2019t know him.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "<JESUS>But I know him because I come from him, and he sent me to
        you.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Then the leaders tried to arrest him; but no one laid a hand on him,
        because his time[[COMMENT(0)]] had not yet come.  '
      comments:
      - number: '7:30 '
        content: Greek <b>his hour.</b>
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Many among the crowds at the Temple believed in him. \u201CAfter
        all,\u201D they said, \u201Cwould you expect the Messiah to do more miraculous
        signs than this man has done?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'When the Pharisees heard that the crowds were whispering such things,
        they and the leading priests sent Temple guards to arrest Jesus. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "But Jesus told them, <JESUS>\u201CI will be with you only a little
        longer. Then I will return to the one who sent me.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "<JESUS>You will search for me but not find me. And you cannot go
        where I am going.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "The Jewish leaders were puzzled by this statement. \u201CWhere is
        he planning to go?\u201D they asked. \u201CIs he thinking of leaving the
        country and going to the Jews in other lands?[[COMMENT(0)]] Maybe he will
        even teach the Greeks! "
      comments:
      - number: '7:35 '
        content: Or <b>the Jews who live among the Greeks?</b>
    - name: '36: Jesus Promises Living Water'
      title: Jesus Promises Living Water
      number: 36
      content: "What does he mean when he says, \u2018You will search for me but
        not find me,\u2019 and \u2018You cannot go where I am going\u2019?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "On the last day, the climax of the festival, Jesus stood and shouted
        to the crowds, <JESUS>\u201CAnyone who is thirsty may come to me!</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "<JESUS>Anyone who believes in me may come and drink! For the Scriptures
        declare, \u2018Rivers of living water will flow from his heart.\u2019\u201D</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '7:37-38 '
        content: "Or <b>\u201CLet anyone who is thirsty come to me and drink. </b><b>For
          the Scriptures declare, \u2018Rivers of living water will flow from the
          heart of anyone who believes in me.\u2019\u201D</b>"
    - name: '39: Division and Unbelief'
      title: Division and Unbelief
      number: 39
      content: "(When he said \u201Cliving water,\u201D he was speaking of the Spirit,
        who would be given to everyone believing in him. But the Spirit had not yet
        been given,[[COMMENT(0)]] because Jesus had not yet entered into his glory.)  "
      comments:
      - number: '7:39 '
        content: Several early manuscripts read <b>But as yet there was no Spirit.
          </b>Still others read <b>But as yet there was no Holy Spirit.</b>
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "When the crowds heard him say this, some of them declared, \u201CSurely
        this man is the Prophet we\u2019ve been expecting.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '7:40 '
        content: See Deut 18:15, 18; Mal 4:5-6.
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: "Others said, \u201CHe is the Messiah.\u201D Still others said, \u201CBut
        he can\u2019t be! Will the Messiah come from Galilee? "
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: "For the Scriptures clearly state that the Messiah will be born of
        the royal line of David, in Bethlehem, the village where King David was born.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '7:42 '
        content: See Mic 5:2.
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'So the crowd was divided about him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: 'Some even wanted him arrested, but no one laid a hand on him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: "When the Temple guards returned without having arrested Jesus, the
        leading priests and Pharisees demanded, \u201CWhy didn\u2019t you bring him
        in?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: "\u201CWe have never heard anyone speak like this!\u201D the guards
        responded.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: "\u201CHave you been led astray, too?\u201D the Pharisees mocked. "
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: "\u201CIs there a single one of us rulers or Pharisees who believes
        in him? "
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: "This foolish crowd follows him, but they are ignorant of the law.
        God\u2019s curse is on them!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: 'Then Nicodemus, the leader who had met with Jesus earlier, spoke
        up. '
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: "\u201CIs it legal to convict a man before he is given a hearing?\u201D
        he asked.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '52: '
      title: 
      number: 52
      content: "They replied, \u201CAre you from Galilee, too? Search the Scriptures
        and see for yourself\u2014no prophet ever comes[[COMMENT(0)]] from Galilee!\u201D----------[The
        most ancient Greek manuscripts do not include John 7:53\u20138:11.]  "
      comments:
      - number: '7:52 '
        content: Some manuscripts read <b>the prophet does not come.</b>
    - name: '53: '
      title: 
      number: 53
      content: Then the meeting broke up, and everybody went home.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: A Woman Caught in Adultery'
      title: A Woman Caught in Adultery
      number: 1
      content: '  Jesus returned to the Mount of Olives, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'but early the next morning he was back again at the Temple. A crowd
        soon gathered, and he sat down and taught them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'As he was speaking, the teachers of religious law and the Pharisees
        brought a woman who had been caught in the act of adultery. They put her
        in front of the crowd.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CTeacher,\u201D they said to Jesus, \u201Cthis woman was caught
        in the act of adultery. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "The law of Moses says to stone her. What do you say?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'They were trying to trap him into saying something they could use
        against him, but Jesus stooped down and wrote in the dust with his finger. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "They kept demanding an answer, so he stood up again and said, <JESUS>\u201CAll
        right, but let the one who has never sinned throw the first stone!\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Then he stooped down again and wrote in the dust.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'When the accusers heard this, they slipped away one by one, beginning
        with the oldest, until only Jesus was left in the middle of the crowd with
        the woman. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Then Jesus stood up again and said to the woman, <JESUS>\u201CWhere
        are your accusers? Didn\u2019t even one of them condemn you?\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: Jesus, the Light of the World'
      title: Jesus, the Light of the World
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CNo, Lord,\u201D she said.And Jesus said, <JESUS>\u201CNeither
        do I. Go and sin no more.\u201D</JESUS>----------  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Jesus spoke to the people once more and said, <JESUS>\u201CI am the
        light of the world. If you follow me, you won\u2019t have to walk in darkness,
        because you will have the light that leads to life.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "The Pharisees replied, \u201CYou are making those claims about yourself!
        Such testimony is not valid.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Jesus told them, <JESUS>\u201CThese claims are valid even though
        I make them about myself. For I know where I came from and where I am going,
        but you don\u2019t know this about me.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: '<JESUS>You judge me by human standards, but I do not judge anyone.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: '<JESUS>And if I did, my judgment would be correct in every respect
        because I am not alone. The Father</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>who sent
        me is with me.</JESUS>  '
      comments:
      - number: '8:16 '
        content: Some manuscripts read <b>The One.</b>
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: '<JESUS>Your own law says that if two people agree about something,
        their witness is accepted as fact.</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '8:17 '
        content: See Deut 19:15.
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "<JESUS>I am one witness, and my Father who sent me is the other.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "\u201CWhere is your father?\u201D they asked.Jesus answered, <JESUS>\u201CSince
        you don\u2019t know who I am, you don\u2019t know who my Father is. If you
        knew me, you would also know my Father.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: The Unbelieving People Warned'
      title: The Unbelieving People Warned
      number: 20
      content: 'Jesus made these statements while he was teaching in the section
        of the Temple known as the Treasury. But he was not arrested, because his
        time[[COMMENT(0)]] had not yet come.  '
      comments:
      - number: '8:20 '
        content: Greek <b>his hour.</b>
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Later Jesus said to them again, <JESUS>\u201CI am going away. You
        will search for me but will die in your sin. You cannot come where I am going.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "The people[[COMMENT(0)]] asked, \u201CIs he planning to commit suicide?
        What does he mean, \u2018You cannot come where I am going\u2019?\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '8:22 '
        content: Greek <b>Jewish people; </b>also in 8:31, 48, 52, 57.
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Jesus continued, <JESUS>\u201CYou are from below; I am from above.
        You belong to this world; I do not.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "<JESUS>That is why I said that you will die in your sins; for unless
        you believe that </JESUS><smallcaps>I Am</smallcaps> who I claim to be,[[COMMENT(0)]] 
        <JESUS>you will die in your sins.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: '8:24 '
        content: Greek <b>unless you believe that I am. </b>See Exod 3:14.
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "\u201CWho are you?\u201D they demanded.Jesus replied, <JESUS>\u201CThe
        one I have always claimed to be.</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '8:25 '
        content: Or <b>Why do I speak to you at all?</b>
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "<JESUS>I have much to say about you and much to condemn, but I won\u2019t.
        For I say only what I have heard from the one who sent me, and he is completely
        truthful.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "But they still didn\u2019t understand that he was talking about his
        Father.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "So Jesus said, <JESUS>\u201CWhen you have lifted up the Son of Man
        on the cross, then you will understand that </JESUS><smallcaps>I Am</smallcaps>
        he.[[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>I do nothing on my own but say only what the Father
        taught me.</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: '8:28 '
        content: "Greek <b>When you have lifted up the Son of Man, then you will
          know that I am. </b>\u201CSon of Man\u201D is a title Jesus used for himself."
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "<JESUS>And the one who sent me is with me\u2014he has not deserted
        me. For I always do what pleases him.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: Jesus and Abraham'
      title: Jesus and Abraham
      number: 30
      content: 'Then many who heard him say these things believed in him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Jesus said to the people who believed in him, <JESUS>\u201CYou are
        truly my disciples if you remain faithful to my teachings.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "<JESUS>And you will know the truth, and the truth will set you free.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "\u201CBut we are descendants of Abraham,\u201D they said. \u201CWe
        have never been slaves to anyone. What do you mean, \u2018You will be set
        free\u2019?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "Jesus replied, <JESUS>\u201CI tell you the truth, everyone who sins
        is a slave of sin.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: '<JESUS>A slave is not a permanent member of the family, but a son
        is part of the family forever.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: '<JESUS>So if the Son sets you free, you are truly free.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "<JESUS>Yes, I realize that you are descendants of Abraham. And yet
        some of you are trying to kill me because there\u2019s no room in your hearts
        for my message.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "<JESUS>I am telling you what I saw when I was with my Father. But
        you are following the advice of your father.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "\u201COur father is Abraham!\u201D they declared.  <JESUS>\u201CNo,\u201D
        </JESUS>Jesus replied, <JESUS>\u201Cfor if you were really the children of
        Abraham, you would follow his example.</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '8:39 '
        content: Some manuscripts read <b>if you are really the children of Abraham,
          follow his example.</b>
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: '<JESUS>Instead, you are trying to kill me because I told you the
        truth, which I heard from God. Abraham never did such a thing.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: "<JESUS>No, you are imitating your real father.\u201D</JESUS>They
        replied, \u201CWe aren\u2019t illegitimate children! God himself is our true
        Father.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: "Jesus told them, <JESUS>\u201CIf God were your Father, you would
        love me, because I have come to you from God. I am not here on my own, but
        he sent me.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: "<JESUS>Why can\u2019t you understand what I am saying? It\u2019s
        because you can\u2019t even hear me!</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: '<JESUS>For you are the children of your father the devil, and you
        love to do the evil things he does. He was a murderer from the beginning.
        He has always hated the truth, because there is no truth in him. When he
        lies, it is consistent with his character; for he is a liar and the father
        of lies.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: "<JESUS>So when I tell the truth, you just naturally don\u2019t believe
        me!</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: "<JESUS>Which of you can truthfully accuse me of sin? And since I
        am telling you the truth, why don\u2019t you believe me?</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: "<JESUS>Anyone who belongs to God listens gladly to the words of God.
        But you don\u2019t listen because you don\u2019t belong to God.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: "The people retorted, \u201CYou Samaritan devil! Didn\u2019t we say
        all along that you were possessed by a demon?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CNo,\u201D </JESUS>Jesus said, <JESUS>\u201CI have
        no demon in me. For I honor my Father\u2014and you dishonor me.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: '<JESUS>And though I have no wish to glorify myself, God is going
        to glorify me. He is the true judge.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: "<JESUS>I tell you the truth, anyone who obeys my teaching will never
        die!\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '52: '
      title: 
      number: 52
      content: "The people said, \u201CNow we know you are possessed by a demon.
        Even Abraham and the prophets died, but you say, \u2018Anyone who obeys my
        teaching will never die!\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '53: '
      title: 
      number: 53
      content: "Are you greater than our father Abraham? He died, and so did the
        prophets. Who do you think you are?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '54: '
      title: 
      number: 54
      content: "Jesus answered, <JESUS>\u201CIf I want glory for myself, it doesn\u2019t
        count. But it is my Father who will glorify me. You say, \u2018He is our
        God,\u2019</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '8:54 '
        content: Some manuscripts read <b>You say he is your God.</b>
    - name: '55: '
      title: 
      number: 55
      content: "<JESUS>but you don\u2019t even know him. I know him. If I said otherwise,
        I would be as great a liar as you! But I do know him and obey him.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '56: '
      title: 
      number: 56
      content: "<JESUS>Your father Abraham rejoiced as he looked forward to my coming.
        He saw it and was glad.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '57: '
      title: 
      number: 57
      content: "The people said, \u201CYou aren\u2019t even fifty years old. How
        can you say you have seen Abraham?[[COMMENT(0)]]\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '8:57 '
        content: Some manuscripts read <b>How can you say Abraham has seen you?</b>
    - name: '58: '
      title: 
      number: 58
      content: "Jesus answered, <JESUS>\u201CI tell you the truth, before Abraham
        was even born, </JESUS><smallcaps>I Am</smallcaps>![[COMMENT(0)]]<JESUS>\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: '8:58 '
        content: Or <b>before Abraham was even born, I have always been alive; </b>Greek
          reads <b>before Abraham was, I am. </b>See Exod 3:14.
    - name: '59: '
      title: 
      number: 59
      content: At that point they picked up stones to throw at him. But Jesus was
        hidden from them and left the Temple.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jesus Heals a Man Born Blind'
      title: Jesus Heals a Man Born Blind
      number: 1
      content: '  As Jesus was walking along, he saw a man who had been blind from
        birth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CRabbi,\u201D his disciples asked him, \u201Cwhy was this man
        born blind? Was it because of his own sins or his parents\u2019 sins?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CIt was not because of his sins or his parents\u2019
        sins,\u201D </JESUS>Jesus answered. <JESUS>\u201CThis happened so the power
        of God could be seen in him.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: '<JESUS>We must quickly carry out the tasks assigned us by the one
        who sent us.</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>The night is coming, and then
        no one can work.</JESUS>  '
      comments:
      - number: '9:4 '
        content: Other manuscripts read <b>I must quickly carry out the tasks assigned
          me by the one who sent me; </b>still others read <b>We must quickly carry
          out the tasks assigned us by the one who sent me.</b>
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "<JESUS>But while I am here in the world, I am the light of the world.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Then he spit on the ground, made mud with the saliva, and spread
        the mud over the blind man\u2019s eyes. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "He told him, <JESUS>\u201CGo wash yourself in the pool of Siloam\u201D</JESUS>
        (Siloam means \u201Csent\u201D). So the man went and washed and came back
        seeing!  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "His neighbors and others who knew him as a blind beggar asked each
        other, \u201CIsn\u2019t this the man who used to sit and beg?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Some said he was, and others said, \u201CNo, he just looks like him!\u201DBut
        the beggar kept saying, \u201CYes, I am the same one!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "They asked, \u201CWho healed you? What happened?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "He told them, \u201CThe man they call Jesus made mud and spread it
        over my eyes and told me, \u2018Go to the pool of Siloam and wash yourself.\u2019
        So I went and washed, and now I can see!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CWhere is he now?\u201D they asked.\u201CI don\u2019t know,\u201D
        he replied.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Then they took the man who had been blind to the Pharisees, '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'because it was on the Sabbath that Jesus had made the mud and healed
        him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "The Pharisees asked the man all about it. So he told them, \u201CHe
        put the mud over my eyes, and when I washed it away, I could see!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Some of the Pharisees said, \u201CThis man Jesus is not from God,
        for he is working on the Sabbath.\u201D Others said, \u201CBut how could
        an ordinary sinner do such miraculous signs?\u201D So there was a deep division
        of opinion among them.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Then the Pharisees again questioned the man who had been blind and
        demanded, \u201CWhat\u2019s your opinion about this man who healed you?\u201DThe
        man replied, \u201CI think he must be a prophet.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'The Jewish leaders still refused to believe the man had been blind
        and could now see, so they called in his parents. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "They asked them, \u201CIs this your son? Was he born blind? If so,
        how can he now see?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "His parents replied, \u201CWe know this is our son and that he was
        born blind, "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "but we don\u2019t know how he can see or who healed him. Ask him.
        He is old enough to speak for himself.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'His parents said this because they were afraid of the Jewish leaders,
        who had announced that anyone saying Jesus was the Messiah would be expelled
        from the synagogue. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "That\u2019s why they said, \u201CHe is old enough. Ask him.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "So for the second time they called in the man who had been blind
        and told him, \u201CGod should get the glory for this,[[COMMENT(0)]] because
        we know this man Jesus is a sinner.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '9:24 '
        content: Or <b>Give glory to God, not to Jesus; </b>Greek reads <b>Give glory
          to God.</b>
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "\u201CI don\u2019t know whether he is a sinner,\u201D the man replied.
        \u201CBut I know this: I was blind, and now I can see!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "\u201CBut what did he do?\u201D they asked. \u201CHow did he heal
        you?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "\u201CLook!\u201D the man exclaimed. \u201CI told you once. Didn\u2019t
        you listen? Why do you want to hear it again? Do you want to become his disciples,
        too?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Then they cursed him and said, \u201CYou are his disciple, but we
        are disciples of Moses! "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "We know God spoke to Moses, but we don\u2019t even know where this
        man comes from.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "\u201CWhy, that\u2019s very strange!\u201D the man replied. \u201CHe
        healed my eyes, and yet you don\u2019t know where he comes from? "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "We know that God doesn\u2019t listen to sinners, but he is ready
        to hear those who worship him and do his will. "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'Ever since the world began, no one has been able to open the eyes
        of someone born blind. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "If this man were not from God, he couldn\u2019t have done it.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: Spiritual Blindness'
      title: Spiritual Blindness
      number: 34
      content: "\u201CYou were born a total sinner!\u201D they answered. \u201CAre
        you trying to teach us?\u201D And they threw him out of the synagogue.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "When Jesus heard what had happened, he found the man and asked, <JESUS>\u201CDo
        you believe in the Son of Man?</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]]<JESUS>\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: '9:35 '
        content: "Some manuscripts read <b>the Son of God? </b>\u201CSon of Man\u201D
          is a title Jesus used for himself."
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "The man answered, \u201CWho is he, sir? I want to believe in him.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CYou have seen him,\u201D </JESUS>Jesus said, <JESUS>\u201Cand
        he is speaking to you!\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "\u201CYes, Lord, I believe!\u201D the man said. And he worshiped
        Jesus.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "Then Jesus told him,[[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>\u201CI entered this world
        to render judgment\u2014to give sight to the blind and to show those who
        think they see</JESUS>[[COMMENT(1)]]  <JESUS>that they are blind.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: '9:38-39a '
        content: "Some manuscripts do not include <b>\u201CYes, Lord, I believe!\u201D
          the man said. And he worshiped Jesus. Then Jesus told him.</b>"
      - number: '9:39b '
        content: Greek <b>those who see.</b>
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "Some Pharisees who were standing nearby heard him and asked, \u201CAre
        you saying we\u2019re blind?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CIf you were blind, you wouldn\u2019t be guilty,\u201D
        </JESUS>Jesus replied. <JESUS>\u201CBut you remain guilty because you claim
        you can see.</JESUS>"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Good Shepherd and His Sheep'
      title: The Good Shepherd and His Sheep
      number: 1
      content: "    <JESUS>\u201CI tell you the truth, anyone who sneaks over the
        wall of a sheepfold, rather than going through the gate, must surely be a
        thief and a robber!</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: '<JESUS>But the one who enters through the gate is the shepherd of
        the sheep.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: '<JESUS>The gatekeeper opens the gate for him, and the sheep recognize
        his voice and come to him. He calls his own sheep by name and leads them
        out.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: '<JESUS>After he has gathered his own flock, he walks ahead of them,
        and they follow him because they know his voice.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "<JESUS>They won\u2019t follow a stranger; they will run from him
        because they don\u2019t know his voice.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Those who heard Jesus use this illustration didn\u2019t understand
        what he meant, "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "so he explained it to them: <JESUS>\u201CI tell you the truth, I
        am the gate for the sheep.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: '<JESUS>All who came before me</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>were
        thieves and robbers. But the true sheep did not listen to them.</JESUS>  '
      comments:
      - number: '10:8 '
        content: Some manuscripts do not include <b>before me.</b>
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: '<JESUS>Yes, I am the gate. Those who come in through me will be saved.</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]] 
        <JESUS>They will come and go freely and will find good pastures.</JESUS>  '
      comments:
      - number: '10:9 '
        content: Or <b>will find safety.</b>
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "<JESUS>The thief\u2019s purpose is to steal and kill and destroy.
        My purpose is to give them a rich and satisfying life.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CI am the good shepherd. The good shepherd sacrifices
        his life for the sheep.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "<JESUS>A hired hand will run when he sees a wolf coming. He will
        abandon the sheep because they don\u2019t belong to him and he isn\u2019t
        their shepherd. And so the wolf attacks them and scatters the flock.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "<JESUS>The hired hand runs away because he\u2019s working only for
        the money and doesn\u2019t really care about the sheep.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CI am the good shepherd; I know my own sheep, and they
        know me,</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: '<JESUS>just as my Father knows me and I know the Father. So I sacrifice
        my life for the sheep.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: '<JESUS>I have other sheep, too, that are not in this sheepfold. I
        must bring them also. They will listen to my voice, and there will be one
        flock with one shepherd.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CThe Father loves me because I sacrifice my life so
        I may take it back again.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "<JESUS>No one can take my life from me. I sacrifice it voluntarily.
        For I have the authority to lay it down when I want to and also to take it
        up again. For this is what my Father has commanded.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'When he said these things, the people[[COMMENT(0)]] were again divided
        in their opinions about him. '
      comments:
      - number: '10:19 '
        content: Greek <b>Jewish people; </b>also in 10:24, 31.
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Some said, \u201CHe\u2019s demon possessed and out of his mind. Why
        listen to a man like that?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: Jesus Claims to Be the Son of God'
      title: Jesus Claims to Be the Son of God
      number: 21
      content: "Others said, \u201CThis doesn\u2019t sound like a man possessed by
        a demon! Can a demon open the eyes of the blind?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'It was now winter, and Jesus was in Jerusalem at the time of Hanukkah,
        the Festival of Dedication. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "He was in the Temple, walking through the section known as Solomon\u2019s
        Colonnade. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "The people surrounded him and asked, \u201CHow long are you going
        to keep us in suspense? If you are the Messiah, tell us plainly.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Jesus replied, <JESUS>\u201CI have already told you, and you don\u2019t
        believe me. The proof is the work I do in my Father\u2019s name.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "<JESUS>But you don\u2019t believe me because you are not my sheep.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: '<JESUS>My sheep listen to my voice; I know them, and they follow
        me.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: '<JESUS>I give them eternal life, and they will never perish. No one
        can snatch them away from me,</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "<JESUS>for my Father has given them to me, and he is more powerful
        than anyone else.</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>No one can snatch them from
        the Father\u2019s hand.</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: '10:29 '
        content: Other manuscripts read <b>for what my Father has given me is more
          powerful than anything; </b>still others read <b>for regarding that which
          my Father has given me, he is greater than all.</b>
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "<JESUS>The Father and I are one.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Once again the people picked up stones to kill him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "Jesus said, <JESUS>\u201CAt my Father\u2019s direction I have done
        many good works. For which one are you going to stone me?\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "They replied, \u201CWe\u2019re stoning you not for any good work,
        but for blasphemy! You, a mere man, claim to be God.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "Jesus replied, <JESUS>\u201CIt is written in your own Scriptures</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]] 
        <JESUS>that God said to certain leaders of the people, \u2018I say, you are
        gods!\u2019</JESUS>[[COMMENT(1)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '10:34a '
        content: Greek <b>your own law.</b>
      - number: '10:34b '
        content: Ps 82:6.
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "<JESUS>And you know that the Scriptures cannot be altered. So if
        those people who received God\u2019s message were called \u2018gods,\u2019</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "<JESUS>why do you call it blasphemy when I say, \u2018I am the Son
        of God\u2019? After all, the Father set me apart and sent me into the world.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "<JESUS>Don\u2019t believe me unless I carry out my Father\u2019s
        work.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "<JESUS>But if I do his work, believe in the evidence of the miraculous
        works I have done, even if you don\u2019t believe me. Then you will know
        and understand that the Father is in me, and I am in the Father.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'Once again they tried to arrest him, but he got away and left them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'He went beyond the Jordan River near the place where John was first
        baptizing and stayed there awhile. '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: "And many followed him. \u201CJohn didn\u2019t perform miraculous
        signs,\u201D they remarked to one another, \u201Cbut everything he said about
        this man has come true.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: And many who were there believed in Jesus.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Raising of Lazarus'
      title: The Raising of Lazarus
      number: 1
      content: '  A man named Lazarus was sick. He lived in Bethany with his sisters,
        Mary and Martha. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "This is the Mary who later poured the expensive perfume on the Lord\u2019s
        feet and wiped them with her hair.[[COMMENT(0)]] Her brother, Lazarus, was
        sick. "
      comments:
      - number: '11:2 '
        content: This incident is recorded in chapter 12.
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "So the two sisters sent a message to Jesus telling him, \u201CLord,
        your dear friend is very sick.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "But when Jesus heard about it he said, <JESUS>\u201CLazarus\u2019s
        sickness will not end in death. No, it happened for the glory of God so that
        the Son of God will receive glory from this.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'So although Jesus loved Martha, Mary, and Lazarus, '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'he stayed where he was for the next two days. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Finally, he said to his disciples, <JESUS>\u201CLet\u2019s go back
        to Judea.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "But his disciples objected. \u201CRabbi,\u201D they said, \u201Conly
        a few days ago the people[[COMMENT(0)]] in Judea were trying to stone you.
        Are you going there again?\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '11:8 '
        content: Greek <b>Jewish people; </b>also in 11:19, 31, 33, 36, 45, 54.
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Jesus replied, <JESUS>\u201CThere are twelve hours of daylight every
        day. During the day people can walk safely. They can see because they have
        the light of this world.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "<JESUS>But at night there is danger of stumbling because they have
        no light.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Then he said, <JESUS>\u201COur friend Lazarus has fallen asleep,
        but now I will go and wake him up.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "The disciples said, \u201CLord, if he is sleeping, he will soon get
        better!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'They thought Jesus meant Lazarus was simply sleeping, but Jesus meant
        Lazarus had died.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "So he told them plainly, <JESUS>\u201CLazarus is dead.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "<JESUS>And for your sakes, I\u2019m glad I wasn\u2019t there, for
        now you will really believe. Come, let\u2019s go see him.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Thomas, nicknamed the Twin,[[COMMENT(0)]] said to his fellow disciples,
        \u201CLet\u2019s go, too\u2014and die with Jesus.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '11:16 '
        content: Greek <b>Thomas, who was called Didymus.</b>
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'When Jesus arrived at Bethany, he was told that Lazarus had already
        been in his grave for four days. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Bethany was only a few miles[[COMMENT(0)]] down the road from Jerusalem, '
      comments:
      - number: '11:18 '
        content: Greek <b>was about 15 stadia </b>[about 2.8 kilometers].
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'and many of the people had come to console Martha and Mary in their
        loss. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'When Martha got word that Jesus was coming, she went to meet him.
        But Mary stayed in the house. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Martha said to Jesus, \u201CLord, if only you had been here, my brother
        would not have died. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "But even now I know that God will give you whatever you ask.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Jesus told her, <JESUS>\u201CYour brother will rise again.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "\u201CYes,\u201D Martha said, \u201Che will rise when everyone else
        rises, at the last day.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Jesus told her, <JESUS>\u201CI am the resurrection and the life.</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]] 
        <JESUS>Anyone who believes in me will live, even after dying.</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: '11:25 '
        content: Some manuscripts do not include <b>and the life.</b>
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "<JESUS>Everyone who lives in me and believes in me will never ever
        die. Do you believe this, Martha?\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "\u201CYes, Lord,\u201D she told him. \u201CI have always believed
        you are the Messiah, the Son of God, the one who has come into the world
        from God.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Then she returned to Mary. She called Mary aside from the mourners
        and told her, \u201CThe Teacher is here and wants to see you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'So Mary immediately went to him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Jesus had stayed outside the village, at the place where Martha met
        him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "When the people who were at the house consoling Mary saw her leave
        so hastily, they assumed she was going to Lazarus\u2019s grave to weep. So
        they followed her there. "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "When Mary arrived and saw Jesus, she fell at his feet and said, \u201CLord,
        if only you had been here, my brother would not have died.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'When Jesus saw her weeping and saw the other people wailing with
        her, a deep anger welled up within him,[[COMMENT(0)]] and he was deeply troubled. '
      comments:
      - number: '11:33 '
        content: Or <b>he was angry in his spirit.</b>
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CWhere have you put him?\u201D </JESUS>he asked them.They
        told him, \u201CLord, come and see.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'Then Jesus wept. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "The people who were standing nearby said, \u201CSee how much he loved
        him!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "But some said, \u201CThis man healed a blind man. Couldn\u2019t he
        have kept Lazarus from dying?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'Jesus was still angry as he arrived at the tomb, a cave with a stone
        rolled across its entrance. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CRoll the stone aside,\u201D </JESUS>Jesus told them.But
        Martha, the dead man\u2019s sister, protested, \u201CLord, he has been dead
        for four days. The smell will be terrible.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "Jesus responded, <JESUS>\u201CDidn\u2019t I tell you that you would
        see God\u2019s glory if you believe?\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: "So they rolled the stone aside. Then Jesus looked up to heaven and
        said, <JESUS>\u201CFather, thank you for hearing me.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: "<JESUS>You always hear me, but I said it out loud for the sake of
        all these people standing here, so that they will believe you sent me.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: "Then Jesus shouted, <JESUS>\u201CLazarus, come out!\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '44: The Plot to Kill Jesus'
      title: The Plot to Kill Jesus
      number: 44
      content: "And the dead man came out, his hands and feet bound in graveclothes,
        his face wrapped in a headcloth. Jesus told them, <JESUS>\u201CUnwrap him
        and let him go!\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: 'Many of the people who were with Mary believed in Jesus when they
        saw this happen. '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: 'But some went to the Pharisees and told them what Jesus had done. '
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: "Then the leading priests and Pharisees called the high council[[COMMENT(0)]]
        together. \u201CWhat are we going to do?\u201D they asked each other. \u201CThis
        man certainly performs many miraculous signs. "
      comments:
      - number: '11:47 '
        content: Greek <b>the Sanhedrin.</b>
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: "If we allow him to go on like this, soon everyone will believe in
        him. Then the Roman army will come and destroy both our Temple[[COMMENT(0)]]
        and our nation.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '11:48 '
        content: Or <b>our position; </b>Greek reads <b>our place.</b>
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: "Caiaphas, who was high priest at that time,[[COMMENT(0)]] said, \u201CYou
        don\u2019t know what you\u2019re talking about! "
      comments:
      - number: '11:49 '
        content: Greek <b>that year; </b>also in 11:51.
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: "You don\u2019t realize that it\u2019s better for you that one man
        should die for the people than for the whole nation to be destroyed.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: 'He did not say this on his own; as high priest at that time he was
        led to prophesy that Jesus would die for the entire nation. '
      comments: []
    - name: '52: '
      title: 
      number: 52
      content: 'And not only for that nation, but to bring together and unite all
        the children of God scattered around the world.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '53: '
      title: 
      number: 53
      content: "So from that time on, the Jewish leaders began to plot Jesus\u2019
        death. "
      comments: []
    - name: '54: '
      title: 
      number: 54
      content: 'As a result, Jesus stopped his public ministry among the people and
        left Jerusalem. He went to a place near the wilderness, to the village of
        Ephraim, and stayed there with his disciples.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '55: '
      title: 
      number: 55
      content: 'It was now almost time for the Jewish Passover celebration, and many
        people from all over the country arrived in Jerusalem several days early
        so they could go through the purification ceremony before Passover began. '
      comments: []
    - name: '56: '
      title: 
      number: 56
      content: "They kept looking for Jesus, but as they stood around in the Temple,
        they said to each other, \u201CWhat do you think? He won\u2019t come for
        Passover, will he?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '57: '
      title: 
      number: 57
      content: Meanwhile, the leading priests and Pharisees had publicly ordered
        that anyone seeing Jesus must report it immediately so they could arrest
        him.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jesus Anointed at Bethany'
      title: Jesus Anointed at Bethany
      number: 1
      content: "  Six days before the Passover celebration began, Jesus arrived in
        Bethany, the home of Lazarus\u2014the man he had raised from the dead. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "A dinner was prepared in Jesus\u2019 honor. Martha served, and Lazarus
        was among those who ate[[COMMENT(0)]] with him. "
      comments:
      - number: '12:2 '
        content: Or <b>who reclined.</b>
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Then Mary took a twelve-ounce jar[[COMMENT(0)]] of expensive perfume
        made from essence of nard, and she anointed Jesus\u2019 feet with it, wiping
        his feet with her hair. The house was filled with the fragrance.  "
      comments:
      - number: '12:3 '
        content: Greek <b>took 1 litra </b>[327 grams].
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'But Judas Iscariot, the disciple who would soon betray him, said, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CThat perfume was worth a year\u2019s wages.[[COMMENT(0)]] It
        should have been sold and the money given to the poor.\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '12:5 '
        content: "Greek <b>worth 300 denarii. </b>A denarius was equivalent to a
          laborer\u2019s full day\u2019s wage."
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Not that he cared for the poor\u2014he was a thief, and since he
        was in charge of the disciples\u2019 money, he often stole some for himself.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Jesus replied, <JESUS>\u201CLeave her alone. She did this in preparation
        for my burial.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "<JESUS>You will always have the poor among you, but you will not
        always have me.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "When all the people[[COMMENT(0)]] heard of Jesus\u2019 arrival, they
        flocked to see him and also to see Lazarus, the man Jesus had raised from
        the dead. "
      comments:
      - number: '12:9 '
        content: Greek <b>Jewish people; </b>also in 12:11.
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Then the leading priests decided to kill Lazarus, too, '
      comments: []
    - name: "11: Jesus\u2019 Triumphant Entry"
      title: "Jesus\u2019 Triumphant Entry"
      number: 11
      content: 'for it was because of him that many of the people had deserted them[[COMMENT(0)]]
        and believed in Jesus.  '
      comments:
      - number: '12:11 '
        content: Or <b>had deserted their traditions; </b>Greek reads <b>had deserted.</b>
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'The next day, the news that Jesus was on the way to Jerusalem swept
        through the city. A large crowd of Passover visitors '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "took palm branches and went down the road to meet him. They shouted,\u201CPraise
        God![[COMMENT(0)]]Blessings on the one who comes in the name of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>!Hail
        to the King of Israel!\u201D[[COMMENT(1)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '12:13a '
        content: "Greek <b>Hosanna, </b>an exclamation of praise adapted from a Hebrew
          expression that means \u201Csave now.\u201D"
      - number: '12:13b '
        content: Ps 118:25-26; Zeph 3:15.
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Jesus found a young donkey and rode on it, fulfilling the prophecy
        that said:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u201CDon\u2019t be afraid, people of Jerusalem.[[COMMENT(0)]]Look,
        your King is coming,riding on a donkey\u2019s colt.\u201D[[COMMENT(1)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '12:15a '
        content: Greek <b>daughter of Zion.</b>
      - number: '12:15b '
        content: Zech 9:9.
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "His disciples didn\u2019t understand at the time that this was a
        fulfillment of prophecy. But after Jesus entered into his glory, they remembered
        what had happened and realized that these things had been written about him.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Many in the crowd had seen Jesus call Lazarus from the tomb, raising
        him from the dead, and they were telling others[[COMMENT(0)]] about it. '
      comments:
      - number: '12:17 '
        content: Greek <b>were testifying.</b>
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "That was the reason so many went out to meet him\u2014because they
        had heard about this miraculous sign. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: Jesus Predicts His Death'
      title: Jesus Predicts His Death
      number: 19
      content: "Then the Pharisees said to each other, \u201CThere\u2019s nothing
        we can do. Look, everyone[[COMMENT(0)]] has gone after him!\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '12:19 '
        content: Greek <b>the world.</b>
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Some Greeks who had come to Jerusalem for the Passover celebration '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "paid a visit to Philip, who was from Bethsaida in Galilee. They said,
        \u201CSir, we want to meet Jesus.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Philip told Andrew about it, and they went together to ask Jesus.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Jesus replied, <JESUS>\u201CNow the time has come for the Son of
        Man</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>to enter into his glory.</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: '12:23 '
        content: "\u201CSon of Man\u201D is a title Jesus used for himself."
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "<JESUS>I tell you the truth, unless a kernel of wheat is planted
        in the soil and dies, it remains alone. But its death will produce many new
        kernels\u2014a plentiful harvest of new lives.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: '<JESUS>Those who love their life in this world will lose it. Those
        who care nothing for their life in this world will keep it for eternity.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: '<JESUS>Anyone who wants to serve me must follow me, because my servants
        must be where I am. And the Father will honor anyone who serves me.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CNow my soul is deeply troubled. Should I pray, \u2018Father,
        save me from this hour\u2019? But this is the very reason I came!</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "<JESUS>Father, bring glory to your name.\u201D</JESUS>Then a voice
        spoke from heaven, saying, \u201CI have already brought glory to my name,
        and I will do so again.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'When the crowd heard the voice, some thought it was thunder, while
        others declared an angel had spoken to him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "Then Jesus told them, <JESUS>\u201CThe voice was for your benefit,
        not mine.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: '<JESUS>The time for judging this world has come, when Satan, the
        ruler of this world, will be cast out.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "<JESUS>And when I am lifted up from the earth, I will draw everyone
        to myself.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'He said this to indicate how he was going to die.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "The crowd responded, \u201CWe understood from Scripture[[COMMENT(0)]]
        that the Messiah would live forever. How can you say the Son of Man will
        die? Just who is this Son of Man, anyway?\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '12:34 '
        content: Greek <b>from the law.</b>
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "Jesus replied, <JESUS>\u201CMy light will shine for you just a little
        longer. Walk in the light while you can, so the darkness will not overtake
        you. Those who walk in the darkness cannot see where they are going.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: The Unbelief of the People'
      title: The Unbelief of the People
      number: 36
      content: "<JESUS>Put your trust in the light while there is still time; then
        you will become children of the light.\u201D</JESUS>After saying these things,
        Jesus went away and was hidden from them.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'But despite all the miraculous signs Jesus had done, most of the
        people still did not believe in him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "This is exactly what Isaiah the prophet had predicted:\u201C<smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        who has believed our message?To whom has the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        revealed his powerful arm?\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '12:38 '
        content: Isa 53:1.
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "But the people couldn\u2019t believe, for as Isaiah also said,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "\u201CThe Lord has blinded their eyesand hardened their hearts\u2014so
        that their eyes cannot see,and their hearts cannot understand,and they cannot
        turn to meand have me heal them.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '12:40 '
        content: Isa 6:10.
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: "Isaiah was referring to Jesus when he said this, because he saw the
        future and spoke of the Messiah\u2019s glory. "
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: "Many people did believe in him, however, including some of the Jewish
        leaders. But they wouldn\u2019t admit it for fear that the Pharisees would
        expel them from the synagogue. "
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'For they loved human praise more than the praise of God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: "Jesus shouted to the crowds, <JESUS>\u201CIf you trust me, you are
        trusting not only me, but also God who sent me.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: '<JESUS>For when you see me, you are seeing the one who sent me.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: '<JESUS>I have come as a light to shine in this dark world, so that
        all who put their trust in me will no longer remain in the dark.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: "<JESUS>I will not judge those who hear me but don\u2019t obey me,
        for I have come to save the world and not to judge it.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: '<JESUS>But all who reject me and my message will be judged on the
        day of judgment by the truth I have spoken.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: "<JESUS>I don\u2019t speak on my own authority. The Father who sent
        me has commanded me what to say and how to say it.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: "<JESUS>And I know his commands lead to eternal life; so I say whatever
        the Father tells me to say.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Jesus Washes His Disciples\u2019 Feet"
      title: "Jesus Washes His Disciples\u2019 Feet"
      number: 1
      content: '  Before the Passover celebration, Jesus knew that his hour had come
        to leave this world and return to his Father. He had loved his disciples
        during his ministry on earth, and now he loved them to the very end.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '13:1 '
        content: Or <b>he showed them the full extent of his love.</b>
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'It was time for supper, and the devil had already prompted Judas,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        son of Simon Iscariot, to betray Jesus. '
      comments:
      - number: '13:2 '
        content: Or <b>the devil had already intended for Judas.</b>
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Jesus knew that the Father had given him authority over everything
        and that he had come from God and would return to God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'So he got up from the table, took off his robe, wrapped a towel around
        his waist, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "and poured water into a basin. Then he began to wash the disciples\u2019
        feet, drying them with the towel he had around him.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "When Jesus came to Simon Peter, Peter said to him, \u201CLord, are
        you going to wash my feet?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Jesus replied, <JESUS>\u201CYou don\u2019t understand now what I
        am doing, but someday you will.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CNo,\u201D Peter protested, \u201Cyou will never ever wash my
        feet!\u201DJesus replied, <JESUS>\u201CUnless I wash you, you won\u2019t
        belong to me.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Simon Peter exclaimed, \u201CThen wash my hands and head as well,
        Lord, not just my feet!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Jesus replied, <JESUS>\u201CA person who has bathed all over does
        not need to wash, except for the feet,</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>to be
        entirely clean. And you disciples are clean, but not all of you.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: '13:10 '
        content: 'Some manuscripts do not include <b>except for the feet.</b>  '
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "For Jesus knew who would betray him. That is what he meant when he
        said, <JESUS>\u201CNot all of you are clean.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "After washing their feet, he put on his robe again and sat down and
        asked, <JESUS>\u201CDo you understand what I was doing?</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "<JESUS>You call me \u2018Teacher\u2019 and \u2018Lord,\u2019 and
        you are right, because that\u2019s what I am.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "<JESUS>And since I, your Lord and Teacher, have washed your feet,
        you ought to wash each other\u2019s feet.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: '<JESUS>I have given you an example to follow. Do as I have done to
        you.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: '<JESUS>I tell you the truth, slaves are not greater than their master.
        Nor is the messenger more important than the one who sends the message.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: Jesus Predicts His Betrayal'
      title: Jesus Predicts His Betrayal
      number: 17
      content: '<JESUS>Now that you know these things, God will bless you for doing
        them.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CI am not saying these things to all of you; I know
        the ones I have chosen. But this fulfills the Scripture that says, \u2018The
        one who eats my food has turned against me.\u2019</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '13:18 '
        content: '  Ps 41:9.  '
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: '<JESUS>I tell you this beforehand, so that when it happens you will
        believe that </JESUS><smallcaps>I Am</smallcaps> the Messiah.[[COMMENT(0)]]<smallcaps>or
        </smallcaps><smallcaps>Greek reads </smallcaps>  '
      comments:
      - number: '13:19 '
        content: "Or <b>that the \u2018<span class=\"ChapterContent_nd__ECPAf\">I
          Am</span>\u2019 has come; </b><b>that I am the <span class=\"ChapterContent_nd__ECPAf\">Lord</span>;
          </b><b>that I am. </b>See Exod 3:14."
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "<JESUS>I tell you the truth, anyone who welcomes my messenger is
        welcoming me, and anyone who welcomes me is welcoming the Father who sent
        me.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Now Jesus was deeply troubled,[[COMMENT(0)]] and he exclaimed, <JESUS>\u201CI
        tell you the truth, one of you will betray me!\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: '13:21 '
        content: Greek <b>was troubled in his spirit.</b>
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'The disciples looked at each other, wondering whom he could mean. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'The disciple Jesus loved was sitting next to Jesus at the table.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '13:23 '
        content: "Greek <b>was reclining on Jesus\u2019 bosom. </b>The \u201Cdisciple
          Jesus loved\u201D was probably John."
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Simon Peter motioned to him to ask, \u201CWho\u2019s he talking about?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "So that disciple leaned over to Jesus and asked, \u201CLord, who
        is it?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Jesus responded, <JESUS>\u201CIt is the one to whom I give the bread
        I dip in the bowl.\u201D</JESUS> And when he had dipped it, he gave it to
        Judas, son of Simon Iscariot. "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "When Judas had eaten the bread, Satan entered into him. Then Jesus
        told him, <JESUS>\u201CHurry and do what you\u2019re going to do.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'None of the others at the table knew what Jesus meant. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Since Judas was their treasurer, some thought Jesus was telling him
        to go and pay for the food or to give some money to the poor. '
      comments: []
    - name: "30: Jesus Predicts Peter\u2019s Denial"
      title: "Jesus Predicts Peter\u2019s Denial"
      number: 30
      content: 'So Judas left at once, going out into the night.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "As soon as Judas left the room, Jesus said, <JESUS>\u201CThe time
        has come for the Son of Man</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>to enter into his
        glory, and God will be glorified because of him.</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: '13:31 '
        content: "\u201CSon of Man\u201D is a title Jesus used for himself."
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: '<JESUS>And since God receives glory because of the Son,</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]] 
        <JESUS>he will give his own glory to the Son, and he will do so at once.</JESUS>  '
      comments:
      - number: '13:32 '
        content: Several early manuscripts do not include <b>And since God receives
          glory because of the Son.</b>
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "<JESUS>Dear children, I will be with you only a little longer. And
        as I told the Jewish leaders, you will search for me, but you can\u2019t
        come where I am going.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: '<JESUS>So now I am giving you a new commandment: Love each other.
        Just as I have loved you, you should love each other.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "<JESUS>Your love for one another will prove to the world that you
        are my disciples.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "Simon Peter asked, \u201CLord, where are you going?\u201DAnd Jesus
        replied, <JESUS>\u201CYou can\u2019t go with me now, but you will follow
        me later.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "\u201CBut why can\u2019t I come now, Lord?\u201D he asked. \u201CI\u2019m
        ready to die for you.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "Jesus answered, <JESUS>\u201CDie for me? I tell you the truth, Peter\u2014before
        the rooster crows tomorrow morning, you will deny three times that you even
        know me.</JESUS>"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jesus, the Way to the Father'
      title: Jesus, the Way to the Father
      number: 1
      content: "    <JESUS>\u201CDon\u2019t let your hearts be troubled. Trust in
        God, and trust also in me.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "<JESUS>There is more than enough room in my Father\u2019s home.</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]] 
        <JESUS>If this were not so, would I have told you that I am going to prepare
        a place for you?</JESUS>[[COMMENT(1)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '14:2a '
        content: "Or <b>There are many rooms in my Father\u2019s house.</b>"
      - number: '14:2b '
        content: Or <b>If this were not so, I would have told you that I am going
          to prepare a place for you. </b>Some manuscripts read <b>If this were not
          so, I would have told you. I am going to prepare a place for you.</b>
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: '<JESUS>When everything is ready, I will come and get you, so that
        you will always be with me where I am.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "<JESUS>And you know the way to where I am going.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CNo, we don\u2019t know, Lord,\u201D Thomas said. \u201CWe have
        no idea where you are going, so how can we know the way?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Jesus told him, <JESUS>\u201CI am the way, the truth, and the life.
        No one can come to the Father except through me.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "<JESUS>If you had really known me, you would know who my Father is.</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]] 
        <JESUS>From now on, you do know him and have seen him!\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: '14:7 '
        content: 'Some manuscripts read <b>If you have really known me, you will
          know who my Father is.</b>  '
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Philip said, \u201CLord, show us the Father, and we will be satisfied.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Jesus replied, <JESUS>\u201CHave I been with you all this time, Philip,
        and yet you still don\u2019t know who I am? Anyone who has seen me has seen
        the Father! So why are you asking me to show him to you?</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "<JESUS>Don\u2019t you believe that I am in the Father and the Father
        is in me? The words I speak are not my own, but my Father who lives in me
        does his work through me.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: '<JESUS>Just believe that I am in the Father and the Father is in
        me. Or at least believe because of the work you have seen me do.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CI tell you the truth, anyone who believes in me will
        do the same works I have done, and even greater works, because I am going
        to be with the Father.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: '<JESUS>You can ask for anything in my name, and I will do it, so
        that the Son can bring glory to the Father.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: Jesus Promises the Holy Spirit'
      title: Jesus Promises the Holy Spirit
      number: 14
      content: '<JESUS>Yes, ask me for anything in my name, and I will do it!</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CIf you love me, obey</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>my
        commandments.</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: '14:15 '
        content: '  Other manuscripts read   <b>you will obey; </b>  still others
          read   <b>you should obey.</b>  '
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: '<JESUS>And I will ask the Father, and he will give you another Advocate,</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]] 
        <JESUS>who will never leave you.</JESUS>  '
      comments:
      - number: '14:16 '
        content: Or <b>Comforter, </b>or <b>Encourager, </b>or <b>Counselor. </b>Greek
          reads <b>Paraclete; </b>also in 14:26.
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "<JESUS>He is the Holy Spirit, who leads into all truth. The world
        cannot receive him, because it isn\u2019t looking for him and doesn\u2019t
        recognize him. But you know him, because he lives with you now and later
        will be in you.</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '14:17 '
        content: Some manuscripts read <b>and is in you.</b>
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "<JESUS>No, I will not abandon you as orphans\u2014I will come to
        you.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: '<JESUS>Soon the world will no longer see me, but you will see me.
        Since I live, you also will live.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: '<JESUS>When I am raised to life again, you will know that I am in
        my Father, and you are in me, and I am in you.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "<JESUS>Those who accept my commandments and obey them are the ones
        who love me. And because they love me, my Father will love them. And I will
        love them and reveal myself to each of them.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Judas (not Judas Iscariot, but the other disciple with that name)
        said to him, \u201CLord, why are you going to reveal yourself only to us
        and not to the world at large?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Jesus replied, <JESUS>\u201CAll who love me will do what I say. My
        Father will love them, and we will come and make our home with each of them.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "<JESUS>Anyone who doesn\u2019t love me will not obey me. And remember,
        my words are not my own. What I am telling you is from the Father who sent
        me.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: '<JESUS>I am telling you these things now while I am still with you.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "<JESUS>But when the Father sends the Advocate as my representative\u2014that
        is, the Holy Spirit\u2014he will teach you everything and will remind you
        of everything I have told you.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CI am leaving you with a gift\u2014peace of mind and
        heart. And the peace I give is a gift the world cannot give. So don\u2019t
        be troubled or afraid.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: '<JESUS>Remember what I told you: I am going away, but I will come
        back to you again. If you really loved me, you would be happy that I am going
        to the Father, who is greater than I am.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: '<JESUS>I have told you these things before they happen so that when
        they do happen, you will believe.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CI don\u2019t have much more time to talk to you, because
        the ruler of this world approaches. He has no power over me,</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "<JESUS>but I will do what the Father requires of me, so that the
        world will know that I love the Father. Come, let\u2019s be going.</JESUS>"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jesus, the True Vine'
      title: Jesus, the True Vine
      number: 1
      content: "    <JESUS>\u201CI am the true grapevine, and my Father is the gardener.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "<JESUS>He cuts off every branch of mine that doesn\u2019t produce
        fruit, and he prunes the branches that do bear fruit so they will produce
        even more.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: '<JESUS>You have already been pruned and purified by the message I
        have given you.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: '<JESUS>Remain in me, and I will remain in you. For a branch cannot
        produce fruit if it is severed from the vine, and you cannot be fruitful
        unless you remain in me.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CYes, I am the vine; you are the branches. Those who
        remain in me, and I in them, will produce much fruit. For apart from me you
        can do nothing.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: '<JESUS>Anyone who does not remain in me is thrown away like a useless
        branch and withers. Such branches are gathered into a pile to be burned.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: '<JESUS>But if you remain in me and my words remain in you, you may
        ask for anything you want, and it will be granted!</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: '<JESUS>When you produce much fruit, you are my true disciples. This
        brings great glory to my Father.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CI have loved you even as the Father has loved me.
        Remain in my love.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "<JESUS>When you obey my commandments, you remain in my love, just
        as I obey my Father\u2019s commandments and remain in his love.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: '<JESUS>I have told you these things so that you will be filled with
        my joy. Yes, your joy will overflow!</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: '<JESUS>This is my commandment: Love each other in the same way I
        have loved you.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "<JESUS>There is no greater love than to lay down one\u2019s life
        for one\u2019s friends.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: '<JESUS>You are my friends if you do what I command.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "<JESUS>I no longer call you slaves, because a master doesn\u2019t
        confide in his slaves. Now you are my friends, since I have told you everything
        the Father told me.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "<JESUS>You didn\u2019t choose me. I chose you. I appointed you to
        go and produce lasting fruit, so that the Father will give you whatever you
        ask for, using my name.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: "17: The World\u2019s Hatred"
      title: "The World\u2019s Hatred"
      number: 17
      content: '<JESUS>This is my command: Love each other.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CIf the world hates you, remember that it hated me
        first.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: '<JESUS>The world would love you as one of its own if you belonged
        to it, but you are no longer part of the world. I chose you to come out of
        the world, so it hates you.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "<JESUS>Do you remember what I told you? \u2018A slave is not greater
        than the master.\u2019 Since they persecuted me, naturally they will persecute
        you. And if they had listened to me, they would listen to you.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: '<JESUS>They will do all this to you because of me, for they have
        rejected the one who sent me.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: '<JESUS>They would not be guilty if I had not come and spoken to them.
        But now they have no excuse for their sin.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: '<JESUS>Anyone who hates me also hates my Father.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "<JESUS>If I hadn\u2019t done such miraculous signs among them that
        no one else could do, they would not be guilty. But as it is, they have seen
        everything I did, yet they still hate me and my Father.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "<JESUS>This fulfills what is written in their Scriptures</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]]<JESUS>:
        \u2018They hated me without cause.\u2019</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: '15:25 '
        content: 'Greek <b>in their law. </b>Pss 35:19; 69:4.  '
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CBut I will send you the Advocate</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]] 
        <JESUS>\u2014the Spirit of truth. He will come to you from the Father and
        will testify all about me.</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: '15:26 '
        content: '  Or   <b>Comforter, </b>  or   <b>Encourager, </b>  or   <b>Counselor.
          </b>  Greek reads   <b>Paraclete.</b>  '
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: <JESUS>And you must also testify about me because you have been with
        me from the beginning of my ministry.</JESUS>
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: "    <JESUS>\u201CI have told you these things so that you won\u2019t
        abandon your faith.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: '<JESUS>For you will be expelled from the synagogues, and the time
        is coming when those who kill you will think they are doing a holy service
        for God.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: '<JESUS>This is because they have never known the Father or me.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: The Work of the Holy Spirit'
      title: The Work of the Holy Spirit
      number: 4
      content: "<JESUS>Yes, I\u2019m telling you these things now, so that when they
        happen, you will remember my warning. I didn\u2019t tell you earlier because
        I was going to be with you for a while longer.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CBut now I am going away to the one who sent me, and
        not one of you is asking where I am going.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "<JESUS>Instead, you grieve because of what I\u2019ve told you.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "<JESUS>But in fact, it is best for you that I go away, because if
        I don\u2019t, the Advocate</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>won\u2019t come.
        If I do go away, then I will send him to you.</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: '16:7 '
        content: Or <b>Comforter, </b>or <b>Encourager, </b>or <b>Counselor. </b>Greek
          reads <b>Paraclete.</b>
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "<JESUS>And when he comes, he will convict the world of its sin, and
        of God\u2019s righteousness, and of the coming judgment.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "<JESUS>The world\u2019s sin is that it refuses to believe in me.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: '<JESUS>Righteousness is available because I go to the Father, and
        you will see me no more.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: '<JESUS>Judgment will come because the ruler of this world has already
        been judged.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CThere is so much more I want to tell you, but you
        can\u2019t bear it now.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: '<JESUS>When the Spirit of truth comes, he will guide you into all
        truth. He will not speak on his own but will tell you what he has heard.
        He will tell you about the future.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: '<JESUS>He will bring me glory by telling you whatever he receives
        from me.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: Sadness Will Be Turned to Joy'
      title: Sadness Will Be Turned to Joy
      number: 15
      content: "<JESUS>All that belongs to the Father is mine; this is why I said,
        \u2018The Spirit will tell you whatever he receives from me.\u2019</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CIn a little while you won\u2019t see me anymore. But
        a little while after that, you will see me again.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Some of the disciples asked each other, \u201CWhat does he mean when
        he says, \u2018In a little while you won\u2019t see me, but then you will
        see me,\u2019 and \u2018I am going to the Father\u2019? "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "And what does he mean by \u2018a little while\u2019? We don\u2019t
        understand.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Jesus realized they wanted to ask him about it, so he said, <JESUS>\u201CAre
        you asking yourselves what I meant? I said in a little while you won\u2019t
        see me, but a little while after that you will see me again.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: '<JESUS>I tell you the truth, you will weep and mourn over what is
        going to happen to me, but the world will rejoice. You will grieve, but your
        grief will suddenly turn to wonderful joy.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: '<JESUS>It will be like a woman suffering the pains of labor. When
        her child is born, her anguish gives way to joy because she has brought a
        new baby into the world.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: '<JESUS>So you have sorrow now, but I will see you again; then you
        will rejoice, and no one can rob you of that joy.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "<JESUS>At that time you won\u2019t need to ask me for anything. I
        tell you the truth, you will ask the Father directly, and he will grant your
        request because you use my name.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "<JESUS>You haven\u2019t done this before. Ask, using my name, and
        you will receive, and you will have abundant joy.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CI have spoken of these matters in figures of speech,
        but soon I will stop speaking figuratively and will tell you plainly all
        about the Father.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "<JESUS>Then you will ask in my name. I\u2019m not saying I will ask
        the Father on your behalf,</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: '<JESUS>for the Father himself loves you dearly because you love me
        and believe that I came from God.</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '16:27 '
        content: Some manuscripts read <b>from the Father.</b>
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "<JESUS>Yes, I came from the Father into the world, and now I will
        leave the world and return to the Father.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Then his disciples said, \u201CAt last you are speaking plainly and
        not figuratively. "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "Now we understand that you know everything, and there\u2019s no need
        to question you. From this we believe that you came from God.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Jesus asked, <JESUS>\u201CDo you finally believe?</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "<JESUS>But the time is coming\u2014indeed it\u2019s here now\u2014when
        you will be scattered, each one going his own way, leaving me alone. Yet
        I am not alone because the Father is with me.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "<JESUS>I have told you all this so that you may have peace in me.
        Here on earth you will have many trials and sorrows. But take heart, because
        I have overcome the world.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Prayer of Jesus'
      title: The Prayer of Jesus
      number: 1
      content: "  After saying all these things, Jesus looked up to heaven and said,
        <JESUS>\u201CFather, the hour has come. Glorify your Son so he can give glory
        back to you.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: '<JESUS>For you have given him authority over everyone. He gives eternal
        life to each one you have given him.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "<JESUS>And this is the way to have eternal life\u2014to know you,
        the only true God, and Jesus Christ, the one you sent to earth.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: '<JESUS>I brought glory to you here on earth by completing the work
        you gave me to do.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: '<JESUS>Now, Father, bring me into the glory we shared before the
        world began.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CI have revealed you</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>to
        the ones you gave me from this world. They were always yours. You gave them
        to me, and they have kept your word.</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: '17:6 '
        content: '  Greek   <b>have revealed your name; </b>  also in 17:26.  '
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: '<JESUS>Now they know that everything I have is a gift from you,</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: '<JESUS>for I have passed on to them the message you gave me. They
        accepted it and know that I came from you, and they believe you sent me.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CMy prayer is not for the world, but for those you
        have given me, because they belong to you.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: '<JESUS>All who are mine belong to you, and you have given them to
        me, so they bring me glory.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: '<JESUS>Now I am departing from the world; they are staying in this
        world, but I am coming to you. Holy Father, you have given me your name;</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]] 
        <JESUS>now protect them by the power of your name so that they will be united
        just as we are.</JESUS>  '
      comments:
      - number: '17:11 '
        content: Some manuscripts read <b>you have given me these [disciples].</b>
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: '<JESUS>During my time here, I protected them by the power of the
        name you gave me.</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>I guarded them so that not
        one was lost, except the one headed for destruction, as the Scriptures foretold.</JESUS>  '
      comments:
      - number: '17:12 '
        content: Some manuscripts read <b>I protected those you gave me, by the power
          of your name.</b>
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CNow I am coming to you. I told them many things while
        I was with them in this world so they would be filled with my joy.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: '<JESUS>I have given them your word. And the world hates them because
        they do not belong to the world, just as I do not belong to the world.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "<JESUS>I\u2019m not asking you to take them out of the world, but
        to keep them safe from the evil one.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: '<JESUS>They do not belong to this world any more than I do.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: '<JESUS>Make them holy by your truth; teach them your word, which
        is truth.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: '<JESUS>Just as you sent me into the world, I am sending them into
        the world.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: '<JESUS>And I give myself as a holy sacrifice for them so they can
        be made holy by your truth.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CI am praying not only for these disciples but also
        for all who will ever believe in me through their message.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "<JESUS>I pray that they will all be one, just as you and I are one\u2014as
        you are in me, Father, and I am in you. And may they be in us so that the
        world will believe you sent me.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CI have given them the glory you gave me, so they may
        be one as we are one.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: '<JESUS>I am in them and you are in me. May they experience such perfect
        unity that the world will know that you sent me and that you love them as
        much as you love me.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: '<JESUS>Father, I want these whom you have given me to be with me
        where I am. Then they can see all the glory you gave me because you loved
        me even before the world began!</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CO righteous Father, the world doesn\u2019t know you,
        but I do; and these disciples know you sent me.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "<JESUS>I have revealed you to them, and I will continue to do so.
        Then your love for me will be in them, and I will be in them.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jesus Is Betrayed and Arrested'
      title: Jesus Is Betrayed and Arrested
      number: 1
      content: '  After saying these things, Jesus crossed the Kidron Valley with
        his disciples and entered a grove of olive trees. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Judas, the betrayer, knew this place, because Jesus had often gone
        there with his disciples. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'The leading priests and Pharisees had given Judas a contingent of
        Roman soldiers and Temple guards to accompany him. Now with blazing torches,
        lanterns, and weapons, they arrived at the olive grove.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Jesus fully realized all that was going to happen to him, so he stepped
        forward to meet them. <JESUS>\u201CWho are you looking for?\u201D </JESUS>he
        asked.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CJesus the Nazarene,\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]] they replied.  <JESUS>\u201C</JESUS><smallcaps>I
        Am</smallcaps> he,\u201D  [[COMMENT(1)]]<smallcaps>  </smallcaps><smallcaps> 
        </smallcaps> Jesus said. (Judas, who betrayed him, was standing with them.) "
      comments:
      - number: '18:5a '
        content: 'Or <b>Jesus of Nazareth; </b>also in 18:7.  '
      - number: '18:5b '
        content: "  Or   <b>\u201CThe \u2018<span class=\"ChapterContent_nd__ECPAf\">I
          Am</span>\u2019 is here\u201D; </b>or   <b>\u201CI am the <span class=\"ChapterContent_nd__ECPAf\">Lord</span>\u201D;
          </b>Greek reads   <b>I am; </b>  also in 18:6, 8. See Exod 3:14.  "
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "As Jesus said <JESUS>\u201C</JESUS><smallcaps>I Am</smallcaps> he,\u201D
        they all drew back and fell to the ground! "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Once more he asked them, <JESUS>\u201CWho are you looking for?\u201D</JESUS>And
        again they replied, \u201CJesus the Nazarene.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CI told you that </JESUS><smallcaps>I Am</smallcaps>
        he,\u201D Jesus said. <JESUS>\u201CAnd since I am the one you want, let these
        others go.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "He did this to fulfill his own statement: <JESUS>\u201CI did not
        lose a single one of those you have given me.\u201D</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '18:9 '
        content: See John 6:39 and 17:12.
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Then Simon Peter drew a sword and slashed off the right ear of Malchus,
        the high priest\u2019s slave. "
      comments: []
    - name: "11: Jesus at the High Priest\u2019s House"
      title: "Jesus at the High Priest\u2019s House"
      number: 11
      content: "But Jesus said to Peter, <JESUS>\u201CPut your sword back into its
        sheath. Shall I not drink from the cup of suffering the Father has given
        me?\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'So the soldiers, their commanding officer, and the Temple guards
        arrested Jesus and tied him up. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'First they took him to Annas, since he was the father-in-law of Caiaphas,
        the high priest at that time.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '18:13 '
        content: Greek <b>that year.</b>
    - name: "14: Peter\u2019s First Denial"
      title: "Peter\u2019s First Denial"
      number: 14
      content: "Caiaphas was the one who had told the other Jewish leaders, \u201CIt\u2019s
        better that one man should die for the people.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Simon Peter followed Jesus, as did another of the disciples. That
        other disciple was acquainted with the high priest, so he was allowed to
        enter the high priest\u2019s courtyard with Jesus. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Peter had to stay outside the gate. Then the disciple who knew the
        high priest spoke to the woman watching at the gate, and she let Peter in. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "The woman asked Peter, \u201CYou\u2019re not one of that man\u2019s
        disciples, are you?\u201D\u201CNo,\u201D he said, \u201CI am not.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: The High Priest Questions Jesus'
      title: The High Priest Questions Jesus
      number: 18
      content: 'Because it was cold, the household servants and the guards had made
        a charcoal fire. They stood around it, warming themselves, and Peter stood
        with them, warming himself.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Inside, the high priest began asking Jesus about his followers and
        what he had been teaching them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Jesus replied, <JESUS>\u201CEveryone knows what I teach. I have preached
        regularly in the synagogues and the Temple, where the people</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]] 
        <JESUS>gather. I have not spoken in secret.</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: '18:20 '
        content: Greek <b>Jewish people; </b>also in 18:38.
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "<JESUS>Why are you asking me this question? Ask those who heard me.
        They know what I said.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Then one of the Temple guards standing nearby slapped Jesus across
        the face. \u201CIs that the way to answer the high priest?\u201D he demanded.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Jesus replied, <JESUS>\u201CIf I said anything wrong, you must prove
        it. But if I\u2019m speaking the truth, why are you beating me?\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: "24: Peter\u2019s Second and Third Denials"
      title: "Peter\u2019s Second and Third Denials"
      number: 24
      content: 'Then Annas bound Jesus and sent him to Caiaphas, the high priest.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Meanwhile, as Simon Peter was standing by the fire warming himself,
        they asked him again, \u201CYou\u2019re not one of his disciples, are you?\u201DHe
        denied it, saying, \u201CNo, I am not.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "But one of the household slaves of the high priest, a relative of
        the man whose ear Peter had cut off, asked, \u201CDidn\u2019t I see you out
        there in the olive grove with Jesus?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: "27: Jesus\u2019 Trial before Pilate"
      title: "Jesus\u2019 Trial before Pilate"
      number: 27
      content: 'Again Peter denied it. And immediately a rooster crowed.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Jesus\u2019 trial before Caiaphas ended in the early hours of the
        morning. Then he was taken to the headquarters of the Roman governor.[[COMMENT(0)]]
        His accusers didn\u2019t go inside because it would defile them, and they
        wouldn\u2019t be allowed to celebrate the Passover. "
      comments:
      - number: '18:28 '
        content: Greek <b>to the Praetorium; </b>also in 18:33.
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "So Pilate, the governor, went out to them and asked, \u201CWhat is
        your charge against this man?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "\u201CWe wouldn\u2019t have handed him over to you if he weren\u2019t
        a criminal!\u201D they retorted.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "\u201CThen take him away and judge him by your own law,\u201D Pilate
        told them.\u201COnly the Romans are permitted to execute someone,\u201D the
        Jewish leaders replied. "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "(This fulfilled Jesus\u2019 prediction about the way he would die.[[COMMENT(0)]])  "
      comments:
      - number: '18:32 '
        content: See John 12:32-33.
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "Then Pilate went back into his headquarters and called for Jesus
        to be brought to him. \u201CAre you the king of the Jews?\u201D he asked
        him.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "Jesus replied, <JESUS>\u201CIs this your own question, or did others
        tell you about me?\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "\u201CAm I a Jew?\u201D Pilate retorted. \u201CYour own people and
        their leading priests brought you to me for trial. Why? What have you done?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "Jesus answered, <JESUS>\u201CMy Kingdom is not an earthly kingdom.
        If it were, my followers would fight to keep me from being handed over to
        the Jewish leaders. But my Kingdom is not of this world.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "Pilate said, \u201CSo you are a king?\u201DJesus responded, <JESUS>\u201CYou
        say I am a king. Actually, I was born and came into the world to testify
        to the truth. All who love the truth recognize that what I say is true.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "\u201CWhat is truth?\u201D Pilate asked. Then he went out again to
        the people and told them, \u201CHe is not guilty of any crime. "
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "But you have a custom of asking me to release one prisoner each year
        at Passover. Would you like me to release this \u2018King of the Jews\u2019?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "But they shouted back, \u201CNo! Not this man. We want Barabbas!\u201D
        (Barabbas was a revolutionary.)"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jesus Sentenced to Death'
      title: Jesus Sentenced to Death
      number: 1
      content: '  Then Pilate had Jesus flogged with a lead-tipped whip. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'The soldiers wove a crown of thorns and put it on his head, and they
        put a purple robe on him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u201CHail! King of the Jews!\u201D they mocked, as they slapped
        him across the face.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Pilate went outside again and said to the people, \u201CI am going
        to bring him out to you now, but understand clearly that I find him not guilty.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then Jesus came out wearing the crown of thorns and the purple robe.
        And Pilate said, \u201CLook, here is the man!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "When they saw him, the leading priests and Temple guards began shouting,
        \u201CCrucify him! Crucify him!\u201D\u201CTake him yourselves and crucify
        him,\u201D Pilate said. \u201CI find him not guilty.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "The Jewish leaders replied, \u201CBy our law he ought to die because
        he called himself the Son of God.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'When Pilate heard this, he was more frightened than ever. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "He took Jesus back into the headquarters[[COMMENT(0)]] again and
        asked him, \u201CWhere are you from?\u201D But Jesus gave no answer. "
      comments:
      - number: '19:9 '
        content: Greek <b>the Praetorium.</b>
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CWhy don\u2019t you talk to me?\u201D Pilate demanded. \u201CDon\u2019t
        you realize that I have the power to release you or crucify you?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Then Jesus said, <JESUS>\u201CYou would have no power over me at
        all unless it were given to you from above. So the one who handed me over
        to you has the greater sin.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then Pilate tried to release him, but the Jewish leaders shouted,
        \u201CIf you release this man, you are no \u2018friend of Caesar.\u2019[[COMMENT(0)]]
        Anyone who declares himself a king is a rebel against Caesar.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '19:12 '
        content: "\u201CFriend of Caesar\u201D is a technical term that refers to
          an ally of the emperor."
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'When they said this, Pilate brought Jesus out to them again. Then
        Pilate sat down on the judgment seat on the platform that is called the Stone
        Pavement (in Hebrew, Gabbatha). '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "It was now about noon on the day of preparation for the Passover.
        And Pilate said to the people,[[COMMENT(0)]] \u201CLook, here is your king!\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '19:14 '
        content: Greek <b>Jewish people; </b>also in 19:20.
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u201CAway with him,\u201D they yelled. \u201CAway with him! Crucify
        him!\u201D\u201CWhat? Crucify your king?\u201D Pilate asked.\u201CWe have
        no king but Caesar,\u201D the leading priests shouted back.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: The Crucifixion'
      title: The Crucifixion
      number: 16
      content: 'Then Pilate turned Jesus over to them to be crucified.So they took
        Jesus away. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Carrying the cross by himself, he went to the place called Place
        of the Skull (in Hebrew, Golgotha). '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'There they nailed him to the cross. Two others were crucified with
        him, one on either side, with Jesus between them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "And Pilate posted a sign on the cross that read, \u201CJesus of Nazareth,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        the King of the Jews.\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '19:19 '
        content: Or <b>Jesus the Nazarene.</b>
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'The place where Jesus was crucified was near the city, and the sign
        was written in Hebrew, Latin, and Greek, so that many people could read it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Then the leading priests objected and said to Pilate, \u201CChange
        it from \u2018The King of the Jews\u2019 to \u2018He said, I am King of the
        Jews.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Pilate replied, \u201CNo, what I have written, I have written.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'When the soldiers had crucified Jesus, they divided his clothes among
        the four of them. They also took his robe, but it was seamless, woven in
        one piece from top to bottom. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "So they said, \u201CRather than tearing it apart, let\u2019s throw
        dice[[COMMENT(0)]] for it.\u201D This fulfilled the Scripture that says,
        \u201CThey divided my garments among themselves and threw dice for my clothing.\u201D[[COMMENT(1)]]
        So that is what they did.  "
      comments:
      - number: '19:24a '
        content: Greek <b>cast lots.</b>
      - number: '19:24b '
        content: Ps 22:18.
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Standing near the cross were Jesus\u2019 mother, and his mother\u2019s
        sister, Mary (the wife of Clopas), and Mary Magdalene. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "When Jesus saw his mother standing there beside the disciple he loved,
        he said to her, <JESUS>\u201CDear woman, here is your son.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: The Death of Jesus'
      title: The Death of Jesus
      number: 27
      content: "And he said to this disciple, <JESUS>\u201CHere is your mother.\u201D</JESUS>
        And from then on this disciple took her into his home.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Jesus knew that his mission was now finished, and to fulfill Scripture
        he said, <JESUS>\u201CI am thirsty.\u201D</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '19:28 '
        content: See Pss 22:15; 69:21.
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'A jar of sour wine was sitting there, so they soaked a sponge in
        it, put it on a hyssop branch, and held it up to his lips. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "When Jesus had tasted it, he said, <JESUS>\u201CIt is finished!\u201D</JESUS>
        Then he bowed his head and gave up his spirit.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "It was the day of preparation, and the Jewish leaders didn\u2019t
        want the bodies hanging there the next day, which was the Sabbath (and a
        very special Sabbath, because it was Passover week). So they asked Pilate
        to hasten their deaths by ordering that their legs be broken. Then their
        bodies could be taken down. "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'So the soldiers came and broke the legs of the two men crucified
        with Jesus. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "But when they came to Jesus, they saw that he was already dead, so
        they didn\u2019t break his legs. "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'One of the soldiers, however, pierced his side with a spear, and
        immediately blood and water flowed out. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: '(This report is from an eyewitness giving an accurate account. He
        speaks the truth so that you also may continue to believe.[[COMMENT(0)]]) '
      comments:
      - number: '19:35 '
        content: Some manuscripts read <b>that you also may believe.</b>
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "These things happened in fulfillment of the Scriptures that say,
        \u201CNot one of his bones will be broken,\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '19:36 '
        content: Exod 12:46; Num 9:12; Ps 34:20.
    - name: '37: The Burial of Jesus'
      title: The Burial of Jesus
      number: 37
      content: "and \u201CThey will look on the one they pierced.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '19:37 '
        content: Zech 12:10.
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "Afterward Joseph of Arimathea, who had been a secret disciple of
        Jesus (because he feared the Jewish leaders), asked Pilate for permission
        to take down Jesus\u2019 body. When Pilate gave permission, Joseph came and
        took the body away. "
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'With him came Nicodemus, the man who had come to Jesus at night.
        He brought about seventy-five pounds[[COMMENT(0)]] of perfumed ointment made
        from myrrh and aloes. '
      comments:
      - number: '19:39 '
        content: Greek <b>100 litras </b>[32.7 kilograms].
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "Following Jewish burial custom, they wrapped Jesus\u2019 body with
        the spices in long sheets of linen cloth. "
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'The place of crucifixion was near a garden, where there was a new
        tomb, never used before. '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: And so, because it was the day of preparation for the Jewish Passover[[COMMENT(0)]]
        and since the tomb was close at hand, they laid Jesus there.
      comments:
      - number: '19:42 '
        content: Greek <b>because of the Jewish day of preparation.</b>
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Resurrection'
      title: The Resurrection
      number: 1
      content: '  Early on Sunday morning,[[COMMENT(0)]] while it was still dark,
        Mary Magdalene came to the tomb and found that the stone had been rolled
        away from the entrance. '
      comments:
      - number: '20:1 '
        content: Greek <b>On the first day of the week.</b>
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "She ran and found Simon Peter and the other disciple, the one whom
        Jesus loved. She said, \u201CThey have taken the Lord\u2019s body out of
        the tomb, and we don\u2019t know where they have put him!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Peter and the other disciple started out for the tomb. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'They were both running, but the other disciple outran Peter and reached
        the tomb first. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "He stooped and looked in and saw the linen wrappings lying there,
        but he didn\u2019t go in. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Then Simon Peter arrived and went inside. He also noticed the linen
        wrappings lying there, '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "while the cloth that had covered Jesus\u2019 head was folded up and
        lying apart from the other wrappings. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Then the disciple who had reached the tomb first also went in, and
        he saw and believed\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "for until then they still hadn\u2019t understood the Scriptures that
        said Jesus must rise from the dead. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: Jesus Appears to Mary Magdalene'
      title: Jesus Appears to Mary Magdalene
      number: 10
      content: 'Then they went home.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Mary was standing outside the tomb crying, and as she wept, she stooped
        and looked in. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'She saw two white-robed angels, one sitting at the head and the other
        at the foot of the place where the body of Jesus had been lying. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CDear woman, why are you crying?\u201D the angels asked her.\u201CBecause
        they have taken away my Lord,\u201D she replied, \u201Cand I don\u2019t know
        where they have put him.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "She turned to leave and saw someone standing there. It was Jesus,
        but she didn\u2019t recognize him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CDear woman, why are you crying?\u201D </JESUS>Jesus
        asked her. <JESUS>\u201CWho are you looking for?\u201D</JESUS>She thought
        he was the gardener. \u201CSir,\u201D she said, \u201Cif you have taken him
        away, tell me where you have put him, and I will go and get him.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CMary!\u201D </JESUS>Jesus said.She turned to him and
        cried out, \u201CRabboni!\u201D (which is Hebrew for \u201CTeacher\u201D).  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CDon\u2019t cling to me,\u201D </JESUS>Jesus said,
        <JESUS>\u201Cfor I haven\u2019t yet ascended to the Father. But go find my
        brothers and tell them, \u2018I am ascending to my Father and your Father,
        to my God and your God.\u2019\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: Jesus Appears to His Disciples'
      title: Jesus Appears to His Disciples
      number: 18
      content: "Mary Magdalene found the disciples and told them, \u201CI have seen
        the Lord!\u201D Then she gave them his message.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "That Sunday evening[[COMMENT(0)]] the disciples were meeting behind
        locked doors because they were afraid of the Jewish leaders. Suddenly, Jesus
        was standing there among them! <JESUS>\u201CPeace be with you,\u201D </JESUS>he
        said. "
      comments:
      - number: '20:19 '
        content: Greek <b>In the evening of that day, the first day of the week.</b>
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'As he spoke, he showed them the wounds in his hands and his side.
        They were filled with joy when they saw the Lord! '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Again he said, <JESUS>\u201CPeace be with you. As the Father has
        sent me, so I am sending you.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Then he breathed on them and said, <JESUS>\u201CReceive the Holy
        Spirit.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: Jesus Appears to Thomas'
      title: Jesus Appears to Thomas
      number: 23
      content: "<JESUS>If you forgive anyone\u2019s sins, they are forgiven. If you
        do not forgive them, they are not forgiven.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'One of the twelve disciples, Thomas (nicknamed the Twin),[[COMMENT(0)]]
        was not with the others when Jesus came. '
      comments:
      - number: '20:24 '
        content: Greek <b>Thomas, who was called Didymus.</b>
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "They told him, \u201CWe have seen the Lord!\u201DBut he replied,
        \u201CI won\u2019t believe it unless I see the nail wounds in his hands,
        put my fingers into them, and place my hand into the wound in his side.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Eight days later the disciples were together again, and this time
        Thomas was with them. The doors were locked; but suddenly, as before, Jesus
        was standing among them. <JESUS>\u201CPeace be with you,\u201D </JESUS>he
        said. "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Then he said to Thomas, <JESUS>\u201CPut your finger here, and look
        at my hands. Put your hand into the wound in my side. Don\u2019t be faithless
        any longer. Believe!\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "\u201CMy Lord and my God!\u201D Thomas exclaimed.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: Purpose of the Book'
      title: Purpose of the Book
      number: 29
      content: "Then Jesus told him, <JESUS>\u201CYou believe because you have seen
        me. Blessed are those who believe without seeing me.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'The disciples saw Jesus do many other miraculous signs in addition
        to the ones recorded in this book. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: But these are written so that you may continue to believe[[COMMENT(0)]]
        that Jesus is the Messiah, the Son of God, and that by believing in him you
        will have life by the power of his name.
      comments:
      - number: '20:31 '
        content: Some manuscripts read <b>that you may believe.</b>
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Epilogue: Jesus Appears to Seven Disciples'
      title: 'Epilogue: Jesus Appears to Seven Disciples'
      number: 1
      content: '  Later, Jesus appeared again to the disciples beside the Sea of
        Galilee.[[COMMENT(0)]] This is how it happened. '
      comments:
      - number: '21:1 '
        content: Greek <b>Sea of Tiberias, </b>another name for the Sea of Galilee.
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Several of the disciples were there\u2014Simon Peter, Thomas (nicknamed
        the Twin),[[COMMENT(0)]] Nathanael from Cana in Galilee, the sons of Zebedee,
        and two other disciples.  "
      comments:
      - number: '21:2 '
        content: Greek <b>Thomas, who was called Didymus.</b>
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Simon Peter said, \u201CI\u2019m going fishing.\u201D\u201CWe\u2019ll
        come, too,\u201D they all said. So they went out in the boat, but they caught
        nothing all night.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "At dawn Jesus was standing on the beach, but the disciples couldn\u2019t
        see who he was. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "He called out, <JESUS>\u201CFellows,</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>have
        you caught any fish?\u201D</JESUS>\u201CNo,\u201D they replied.  "
      comments:
      - number: '21:5 '
        content: Greek <b>Children.</b>
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Then he said, <JESUS>\u201CThrow out your net on the right-hand side
        of the boat, and you\u2019ll get some!\u201D</JESUS> So they did, and they
        couldn\u2019t haul in the net because there were so many fish in it.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Then the disciple Jesus loved said to Peter, \u201CIt\u2019s the
        Lord!\u201D When Simon Peter heard that it was the Lord, he put on his tunic
        (for he had stripped for work), jumped into the water, and headed to shore. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'The others stayed with the boat and pulled the loaded net to the
        shore, for they were only about a hundred yards[[COMMENT(0)]] from shore. '
      comments:
      - number: '21:8 '
        content: Greek <b>200 cubits </b>[90 meters].
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "When they got there, they found breakfast waiting for them\u2014fish
        cooking over a charcoal fire, and some bread.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CBring some of the fish you\u2019ve just caught,\u201D
        </JESUS>Jesus said. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "So Simon Peter went aboard and dragged the net to the shore. There
        were 153 large fish, and yet the net hadn\u2019t torn.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CNow come and have some breakfast!\u201D </JESUS>Jesus
        said. None of the disciples dared to ask him, \u201CWho are you?\u201D They
        knew it was the Lord. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Then Jesus served them the bread and the fish. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'This was the third time Jesus had appeared to his disciples since
        he had been raised from the dead.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "After breakfast Jesus asked Simon Peter, <JESUS>\u201CSimon son of
        John, do you love me more than these?</JESUS>[[COMMENT(0)]]<JESUS>\u201D</JESUS>\u201CYes,
        Lord,\u201D Peter replied, \u201Cyou know I love you.\u201D  <JESUS>\u201CThen
        feed my lambs,\u201D </JESUS>Jesus told him.  "
      comments:
      - number: '21:15 '
        content: 'Or <b>more than these others do?</b>  '
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Jesus repeated the question: <JESUS>\u201CSimon son of John, do you
        love me?\u201D</JESUS>\u201CYes, Lord,\u201D Peter said, \u201Cyou know I
        love you.\u201D  <JESUS>\u201CThen take care of my sheep,\u201D </JESUS>Jesus
        said.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "A third time he asked him, <JESUS>\u201CSimon son of John, do you
        love me?\u201D</JESUS>Peter was hurt that Jesus asked the question a third
        time. He said, \u201CLord, you know everything. You know that I love you.\u201DJesus
        said, <JESUS>\u201CThen feed my sheep.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CI tell you the truth, when you were young, you were
        able to do as you liked; you dressed yourself and went wherever you wanted
        to go. But when you are old, you will stretch out your hands, and others</JESUS> 
        [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>will dress you and take you where you don\u2019t want
        to go.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: '21:18 '
        content: '  Some manuscripts read   <b>and another one.</b>  '
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Jesus said this to let him know by what kind of death he would glorify
        God. Then Jesus told him, <JESUS>\u201CFollow me.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Peter turned around and saw behind them the disciple Jesus loved\u2014the
        one who had leaned over to Jesus during supper and asked, \u201CLord, who
        will betray you?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Peter asked Jesus, \u201CWhat about him, Lord?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Jesus replied, <JESUS>\u201CIf I want him to remain alive until I
        return, what is that to you? As for you, follow me.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "So the rumor spread among the community of believers[[COMMENT(0)]]
        that this disciple wouldn\u2019t die. But that isn\u2019t what Jesus said
        at all. He only said, <JESUS>\u201CIf I want him to remain alive until I
        return, what is that to you?\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: '21:23 '
        content: Greek <b>the brothers.</b>
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'This disciple is the one who testifies to these events and has recorded
        them here. And we know that his account of these things is accurate.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: Jesus also did many other things. If they were all written down, I
        suppose the whole world could not contain the books that would be written.
      comments: []
